var book = {
	"name": "1 Chronicles",
	"numChapters": 29,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10254A\"></sup>Adam, Seth, Enosh;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10255B\"></sup>Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Noah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10257C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10257C\"></sup>Shem, Ham, and Japheth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10258D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10258D\"></sup>The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Rodanim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10261E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10261E\"></sup>The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put, and Canaan.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raamah, and Sabteca. The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Cush fathered Nimrod. He was the first on earth to be a mighty man.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10264F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10264F\"></sup>Egypt fathered Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Pathrusim, Casluhim (from whom the Philistines came), and Caphtorim.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Canaan fathered Sidon his firstborn and Heth,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10270G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10270G\"></sup>The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram. And the sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Meshech.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Arpachshad fathered Shelah, and Shelah fathered Eber.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg (for in his days the earth was divided), and his brother's name was Joktan.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Obal, Abimael, Sheba,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10277H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10277H\"></sup>Shem, Arpachshad, Shelah;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Eber, Peleg, Reu;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Serug, Nahor, Terah;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Abram, that is, Abraham.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Abraham: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10281I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10281I\"></sup>Isaac and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10281J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10281J\"></sup>Ishmael.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10282K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10282K\"></sup>These are their genealogies: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth, and Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10285L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10285L\"></sup>The sons of Keturah, Abraham's concubine: she bore Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. The sons of Jokshan: Sheba and Dedan.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Midian: Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the descendants of Keturah.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Abraham fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10287M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10287M\"></sup>Isaac. The sons of Isaac: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10287N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10287N\"></sup>Esau and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10287O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10287O\"></sup>Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10288P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10288P\"></sup>The sons of Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, Kenaz, and of Timna, Amalek.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10291Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10291Q\"></sup>The sons of Seir: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Lotan: Hori and Hemam; and Lotan's sister was Timna.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam. The sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The son of Anah: Dishon. The sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan. The sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10296R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10296R\"></sup>These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the people of Israel: Bela the son of Beor, the name of his city being Dinhabah.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10297S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10297S\"></sup>Bozrah reigned in his place.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10298T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10298T\"></sup>Temanites reigned in his place.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the country of Moab, reigned in his place, the name of his city being Avith.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth on the Euphrates reigned in his place.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Shaul died, and Baal-hanan, the son of Achbor, reigned in his place.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Baal-hanan died, and Hadad reigned in his place, the name of his city being Pai; and his wife's name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>And Hadad died.The chiefs of Edom were: chiefs Timna, Alvah, Jetheth,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Magdiel, and Iram; these are the chiefs of Edom."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>These are the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10308A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10308A\"></sup>Israel: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10308B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10308B\"></sup>Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10308C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10308C\"></sup>Issachar, Zebulun,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10309D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10309D\"></sup>Dan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10309E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10309E\"></sup>Joseph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10309F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10309F\"></sup>Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10309G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10309G\"></sup>Naphtali, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10309H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10309H\"></sup>Gad, and Asher.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10310I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10310I\"></sup>The sons of Judah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10310J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10310J\"></sup>Er, Onan and Shelah; these three Bath-shua the Canaanite bore to him. Now Er, Judah's firstborn, was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he put him to death.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>His daughter-in-law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10311K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10311K\"></sup>Tamar also bore him Perez and Zerah. Judah had five sons in all.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10312L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10312L\"></sup>sons of Perez: Hezron and Hamul.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Zerah: Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Dara, five in all.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The son of Carmi: Achan, the troubler of Israel, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10314M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10314M\"></sup>broke faith in the matter of the devoted thing;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and Ethan's son was Azariah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Hezron that were born to him: Jerahmeel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10316N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10316N\"></sup>Ram, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10316O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10316O\"></sup>Chelubai.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10317P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10317P\"></sup>Ram fathered Amminadab, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10317Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10317Q\"></sup>Amminadab fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10317R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10317R\"></sup>Nahshon, prince of the sons of Judah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Nahshon fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10318S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10318S\"></sup>Salmon, Salmon fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10318T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10318T\"></sup>Boaz,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Boaz fathered Obed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10319U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10319U\"></sup>Obed fathered Jesse.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10320V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10320V\"></sup>Jesse fathered Eliab his firstborn, Abinadab the second, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10320W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10320W\"></sup>Shimea the third,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ozem the sixth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10322X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10322X\"></sup>David the seventh.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And their sisters were Zeruiah and Abigail. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10323Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10323Y\"></sup>The sons of Zeruiah: Abishai, Joab, and Asahel, three.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10324Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10324Z\"></sup>Abigail bore Amasa, and the father of Amasa was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10324AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10324AA\"></sup>Jether the Ishmaelite.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10325AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10325AB\"></sup>Caleb the son of Hezron fathered children by his wife Azubah, and by Jerioth; and these were her sons: Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When Azubah died, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10326AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10326AC\"></sup>Caleb married <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10326AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10326AD\"></sup>Ephrath, who bore him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10326AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10326AE\"></sup>Hur.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Hur fathered Uri, and Uri fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10327AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10327AF\"></sup>Bezalel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10328AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10328AG\"></sup>Machir the father of Gilead, whom he married when he was sixty years old, and she bore him Segub.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Segub fathered Jair, who had twenty-three cities in the land of Gilead.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10330AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10330AH\"></sup>But Geshur and Aram took from them Havvoth-jair, Kenath, and its villages, sixty towns. All these were descendants of Machir, the father of Gilead.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After the death of Hezron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10331AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10331AI\"></sup>Caleb went in to Ephrathah, the wife of Hezron his father, and she bore him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10331AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10331AJ\"></sup>Ashhur, the father of Tekoa.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10332AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10332AK\"></sup>Jerahmeel, the firstborn of Hezron: Ram, his firstborn, Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Jerahmeel also had another wife, whose name was Atarah; she was the mother of Onam.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Ram, the firstborn of Jerahmeel: Maaz, Jamin, and Eker.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Onam: Shammai and Jada. The sons of Shammai: Nadab and Abishur.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The name of Abishur's wife was Abihail, and she bore him Ahban and Molid.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The sons of Nadab: Seled and Appaim; and Seled died childless.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The son of Appaim: Ishi. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10338AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10338AL\"></sup>The son of Ishi: Sheshan. The son of Sheshan: Ahlai.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The sons of Jada, Shammai's brother: Jether and Jonathan; and Jether died childless.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Jonathan: Peleth and Zaza. These were the descendants of Jerahmeel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now Sheshan had no sons, only daughters, but Sheshan had an Egyptian slave whose name was Jarha.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So Sheshan gave his daughter in marriage to Jarha his slave, and she bore him Attai.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Attai fathered Nathan, and Nathan fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10343AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10343AM\"></sup>Zabad.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10344AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10344AN\"></sup>Zabad fathered Ephlal, and Ephlal fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10344AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10344AO\"></sup>Obed.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Obed fathered Jehu, and Jehu fathered Azariah.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Azariah fathered Helez, and Helez fathered Eleasah.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Eleasah fathered Sismai, and Sismai fathered Shallum.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Shallum fathered Jekamiah, and Jekamiah fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10348AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10348AP\"></sup>Elishama.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10349AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10349AQ\"></sup>Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel: Mareshah his firstborn, who fathered Ziph. The son of Mareshah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10349AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10349AR\"></sup>Hebron.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The sons of Hebron: Korah, Tappuah, Rekem and Shema.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Shema fathered Raham, the father of Jorkeam; and Rekem fathered Shammai.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The son of Shammai: Maon; and Maon fathered Beth-zur.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Ephah also, Caleb's concubine, bore Haran, Moza, and Gazez; and Haran fathered Gazez.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>The sons of Jahdai: Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and Shaaph.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Maacah, Caleb's concubine, bore Sheber and Tirhanah.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>She also bore Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbenah and the father of Gibea; and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10356AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10356AS\"></sup>daughter of Caleb was Achsah.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>These were the descendants of Caleb.The sons of Hur the firstborn of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10357AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10357AT\"></sup>Ephrathah: Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10358AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10358AU\"></sup>Salma, the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth-gader.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim had other sons: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10359AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10359AV\"></sup>Haroeh, half of the Menuhoth.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And the clans of Kiriath-jearim: the Ithrites, the Puthites, the Shumathites, and the Mishraites; from these came the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10360AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10360AW\"></sup>Zorathites and the Eshtaolites.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>The sons of Salma: Bethlehem, the Netophathites, Atroth-beth-joab and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>The clans also of the scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites, the Shimeathites and the Sucathites. These are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10362AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10362AX\"></sup>Kenites who came from Hammath, the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10362AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10362AY\"></sup>the house of Rechab."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10363A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10363A\"></sup>These are the sons of David who were born to him in Hebron: the firstborn, Amnon, by Ahinoam the Jezreelite; the second, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10363B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10363B\"></sup>Daniel, by Abigail the Carmelite,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the third, Absalom, whose mother was Maacah, the daughter of Talmai, king of Geshur; the fourth, Adonijah, whose mother was Haggith;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the fifth, Shephatiah, by Abital; the sixth, Ithream, by his wife Eglah;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>six were born to him in Hebron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10366C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10366C\"></sup>where he reigned for seven years and six months. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10366D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10366D\"></sup>And he reigned thirty-three years in Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10367E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10367E\"></sup>These were born to him in Jerusalem: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10367F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10367F\"></sup>Shimea, Shobab, Nathan and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10367G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10367G\"></sup>Solomon, four by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10367H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10367H\"></sup>Bath-shua, the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10367I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10367I\"></sup>Ammiel;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>then Ibhar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10368J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10368J\"></sup>Elishama, Eliphelet,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Elishama, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10370K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10370K\"></sup>Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All these were David's sons, besides the sons of the concubines, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10371L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10371L\"></sup>and Tamar was their sister.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The son of Solomon was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10372M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10372M\"></sup>Rehoboam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10372N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10372N\"></sup>Abijah his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10372O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10372O\"></sup>Asa his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10372P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10372P\"></sup>Jehoshaphat his son,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10373Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10373Q\"></sup>Joram his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10373R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10373R\"></sup>Ahaziah his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10373S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10373S\"></sup>Joash his son,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10374T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10374T\"></sup>Amaziah his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10374U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10374U\"></sup>Azariah his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10374V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10374V\"></sup>Jotham his son,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10375W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10375W\"></sup>Ahaz his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10375X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10375X\"></sup>Hezekiah his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10375Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10375Y\"></sup>Manasseh his son,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10376Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10376Z\"></sup>Amon his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10376AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10376AA\"></sup>Josiah his son.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of Josiah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10377AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10377AB\"></sup>Johanan the firstborn, the second <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10377AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10377AC\"></sup>Jehoiakim, the third <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10377AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10377AD\"></sup>Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The descendants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10378AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10378AE\"></sup>Jehoiakim: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10378AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10378AF\"></sup>Jeconiah his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10378AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10378AG\"></sup>Zedekiah his son;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the sons of Jeconiah, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10379AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10379AH\"></sup>captive: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10379AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10379AI\"></sup>Shealtiel his son,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama and Nedabiah;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and the sons of Pedaiah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10381AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10381AJ\"></sup>Zerubbabel and Shimei; and the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10381AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10381AK\"></sup>Zerubbabel: Meshullam and Hananiah, and Shelomith was their sister;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Hashubah, Ohel, Berechiah, Hasadiah, and Jushab-hesed, five.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Hananiah: Pelatiah and Jeshaiah, his son Rephaiah, his son Arnan, his son Obadiah, his son Shecaniah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The son of Shecaniah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10384AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10384AL\"></sup>Shemaiah. And the sons of Shemaiah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10384AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10384AM\"></sup>Hattush, Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat, six.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Neariah: Elioenai, Hizkiah, and Azrikam, three.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Elioenai: Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah, and Anani, seven."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10387A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10387A\"></sup>The sons of Judah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10387B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10387B\"></sup>Perez, Hezron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10387C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10387C\"></sup>Carmi, Hur, and Shobal.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10388D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10388D\"></sup>Reaiah the son of Shobal fathered Jahath, and Jahath fathered Ahumai and Lahad. These were the clans of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10388E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10388E\"></sup>Zorathites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These were the sons of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash; and the name of their sister was Hazzelelponi,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10390F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10390F\"></sup>Penuel fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10390G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10390G\"></sup>Gedor, and Ezer fathered Hushah. These were the sons of Hur, the firstborn of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10390H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10390H\"></sup>Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10391I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10391I\"></sup>Ashhur, the father of Tekoa, had two wives, Helah and Naarah;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Haahashtari. These were the sons of Naarah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Helah: Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Koz fathered Anub, Zobebah, and the clans of Aharhel, the son of Harum.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jabez was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10395J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10395J\"></sup>more honorable than his brothers; and his mother called his name Jabez, saying, “Because I bore him in pain.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jabez called upon the God of Israel, saying, “Oh that you would bless me and enlarge my border, and that your hand might be with me, and that you would keep me from harm so that it might not bring me pain!” And God granted what he asked.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Chelub, the brother of Shuhah, fathered Mehir, who fathered Eshton.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Eshton fathered Beth-rapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah, the father of Ir-nahash. These are the men of Recah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10399K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10399K\"></sup>Kenaz: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10399L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10399L\"></sup>Othniel and Seraiah; and the sons of Othniel: Hathath and Meonothai.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Meonothai fathered Ophrah; and Seraiah fathered Joab, the father of Ge-harashim, so-called because they were craftsmen.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10401M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10401M\"></sup>Caleb the son of Jephunneh: Iru, Elah, and Naam; and the son of Elah: Kenaz.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Jehallelel: Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Ezrah: Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. These are the sons of Bithiah, the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered married; and she conceived and bore Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah, the father of Eshtemoa.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And his Judahite wife bore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10404N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10404N\"></sup>Jered the father of Gedor, Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, were the fathers of Keilah the Garmite and Eshtemoa the Maacathite.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sons of Shimon: Amnon, Rinnah, Ben-hanan, and Tilon. The sons of Ishi: Zoheth and Ben-zoheth.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10407O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10407O\"></sup>Shelah the son of Judah: Er the father of Lecah, Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the clans of the house of linen workers at Beth-ashbea;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who ruled in Moab and returned to Lehem (now the records are ancient).",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These were the potters who were inhabitants of Netaim and Gederah. They lived there in the king's service.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10410P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10410P\"></sup>The sons of Simeon: Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Shallum was his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of Mishma: Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers did not have many children, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10413Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10413Q\"></sup>nor did all their clan multiply <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10413R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10413R\"></sup>like the men of Judah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10414S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10414S\"></sup>They lived in Beersheba, Moladah, Hazar-shual,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10415T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10415T\"></sup>Bilhah, Ezem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10415U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10415U\"></sup>Tolad,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10416V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10416V\"></sup>Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Beth-marcaboth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10417W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10417W\"></sup>Hazar-susim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10417X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10417X\"></sup>Beth-biri, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10417Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10417Y\"></sup>Shaaraim. These were their cities until David reigned.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And their villages were Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen, and Ashan, five cities,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>along with all their villages that were around these cities as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10419Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10419Z\"></sup>Baal. These were their settlements, and they kept a genealogical record.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah the son of Amaziah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Joel, Jehu the son of Joshibiah, son of Seraiah, son of Asiel,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Ziza the son of Shiphi, son of Allon, son of Jedaiah, son of Shimri, son of Shemaiah—",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>these mentioned by name were princes in their clans, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10424AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10424AA\"></sup>and their fathers' houses increased greatly.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They journeyed to the entrance of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10425AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10425AB\"></sup>Gedor, to the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>where they found rich, good pasture, and the land was very broad, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10426AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10426AC\"></sup>quiet, and peaceful, for the former inhabitants there belonged to Ham.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10427AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10427AD\"></sup>These, registered by name, came in the days of Hezekiah, king of Judah, and destroyed their tents and the Meunites who were found there, and marked them for destruction to this day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10427AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10427AE\"></sup>and settled in their place, because there was pasture there for their flocks.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And some of them, five hundred men of the Simeonites, went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10428AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10428AF\"></sup>Mount Seir, having as their leaders Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And they defeated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10429AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10429AG\"></sup>the remnant of the Amalekites who had escaped, and they have lived there to this day."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10430A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10430A\"></sup>for he was the firstborn, but because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10430B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10430B\"></sup>he defiled his father's couch, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10430C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10430C\"></sup>his birthright was given to the sons of Joseph the son of Israel, so that he could not be enrolled as the oldest son;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10431D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10431D\"></sup>though Judah became strong among his brothers and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10431E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10431E\"></sup>chief came from him, yet the birthright belonged to Joseph),",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10432F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10432F\"></sup>sons of Reuben, the firstborn of Israel: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Joel: Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Beerah his son, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10435G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10435G\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria carried away into exile; he was a chief of the Reubenites.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And his kinsmen by their clans, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10436H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10436H\"></sup>when the genealogy of their generations was recorded: the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and Bela the son of Azaz, son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10437I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10437I\"></sup>Shema, son of Joel, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10437J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10437J\"></sup>Aroer, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10437K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10437K\"></sup>Nebo and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10437L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10437L\"></sup>Baal-meon.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He also lived to the east as far as the entrance of the desert this side of the Euphrates, because their livestock had multiplied <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10438M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10438M\"></sup>in the land of Gilead.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And in the days of Saul they waged war against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10439N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10439N\"></sup>Hagrites, who fell into their hand. And they lived in their tents throughout all the region east of Gilead.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of Gad lived over against them in the land of Bashan as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10440O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10440O\"></sup>Salecah:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joel the chief, Shapham the second, Janai, and Shaphat in Bashan.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And their kinsmen according to their fathers' houses: Michael, Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia and Eber, seven.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These were the sons of Abihail the son of Huri, son of Jaroah, son of Gilead, son of Michael, son of Jeshishai, son of Jahdo, son of Buz.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ahi the son of Abdiel, son of Guni, was chief in their fathers' houses,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and they lived in Gilead, in Bashan and in its towns, and in all the pasturelands of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10445P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10445P\"></sup>Sharon to their limits.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All of these were recorded in genealogies in the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10446Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10446Q\"></sup>Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10446R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10446R\"></sup>Jeroboam king of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh had valiant men who carried shield and sword, and drew the bow, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10447S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10447S\"></sup>expert in war, 44,760, able to go to war.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They waged war against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10448T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10448T\"></sup>Hagrites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10448U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10448U\"></sup>Jetur, Naphish, and Nodab.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And when they prevailed over them, the Hagrites and all who were with them were given into their hands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10449V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10449V\"></sup>for they cried out to God in the battle, and he granted their urgent plea <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10449W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10449W\"></sup>because they trusted in him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They carried off their livestock: 50,000 of their camels, 250,000 sheep, 2,000 donkeys, and 100,000 men alive.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For many fell, because the war was of God. And they lived <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10451X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10451X\"></sup>in their place until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10451Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10451Y\"></sup>the exile.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The members of the half-tribe of Manasseh lived in the land. They were very numerous from Bashan to Baal-hermon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10452Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10452Z\"></sup>Senir, and Mount Hermon.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These were the heads of their fathers' houses: Epher, Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty warriors, famous men, heads of their fathers' houses.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But they broke faith with the God of their fathers, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10454AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10454AA\"></sup>whored <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10454AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10454AB\"></sup>after the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God had destroyed before them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10455AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10455AC\"></sup>Pul king of Assyria, the spirit of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10455AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10455AD\"></sup>Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, and he took them into exile, namely, the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, and brought them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10455AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10455AE\"></sup>to Halah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10455AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10455AF\"></sup>Habor, Hara, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10455AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10455AG\"></sup>the river Gozan, to this day."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10456A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10456A\"></sup>The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10457B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10457B\"></sup>The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10458C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10458C\"></sup>The children of Amram: Aaron, Moses, and Miriam. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10458D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10458D\"></sup>The sons of Aaron: Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10459E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10459E\"></sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10459F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10459F\"></sup>Eleazar fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10459G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10459G\"></sup>Phinehas, Phinehas fathered Abishua,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Abishua fathered Bukki, Bukki fathered Uzzi,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Uzzi fathered Zerahiah, Zerahiah fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10461H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10461H\"></sup>Meraioth,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Meraioth fathered Amariah, Amariah fathered Ahitub,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10463I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10463I\"></sup>Ahitub fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10463J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10463J\"></sup>Zadok, Zadok fathered Ahimaaz,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ahimaaz fathered Azariah, Azariah fathered Johanan,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and Johanan fathered Azariah (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10465K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10465K\"></sup>it was he who served as priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10465L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10465L\"></sup>in the house that Solomon built in Jerusalem).",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10466M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10466M\"></sup>Azariah fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10466N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10466N\"></sup>Amariah, Amariah fathered Ahitub,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Ahitub fathered Zadok, Zadok fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10467O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10467O\"></sup>Shallum,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Shallum fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10468P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10468P\"></sup>Hilkiah, Hilkiah fathered Azariah,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Azariah fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10469Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10469Q\"></sup>Seraiah, Seraiah fathered Jehozadak;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10470R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10470R\"></sup>Jehozadak went into exile when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent Judah and Jerusalem into exile <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10470S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10470S\"></sup>by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup> The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10471T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10471T\"></sup>sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And these are the names of the sons of Gershom: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10472U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10472U\"></sup>Libni and Shimei.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10473V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10473V\"></sup>The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10474W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10474W\"></sup>The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the clans of the Levites according to their fathers.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10475X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10475X\"></sup>Of Gershom: Libni his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10475Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10475Y\"></sup>Jahath his son, Zimmah his son,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeatherai his son.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10477Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10477Z\"></sup>The sons of Kohath: Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Elkanah his son, Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of Elkanah: Amasai and Ahimoth,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Elkanah his son, Zophai his son, Nahath his son,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah his son.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Samuel: Joel his firstborn, the second Abijah.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10484AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10484AA\"></sup>The sons of Merari: Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his son,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, and Asaiah his son.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These are the men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10486AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10486AB\"></sup>whom David put in charge of the service of song in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10486AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10486AC\"></sup>after the ark rested there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They ministered with song before the tabernacle of the tent of meeting until Solomon built the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem, and they performed their service according to their order.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>These are the men who served and their sons. Of the sons of the Kohathites: Heman the singer the son of Joel, son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10488AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10488AD\"></sup>Samuel,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>son of Elkanah, son of Jeroham, son of Eliel, son of Toah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>son of Zuph, son of Elkanah, son of Mahath, son of Amasai,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>son of Elkanah, son of Joel, son of Azariah, son of Zephaniah,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>son of Tahath, son of Assir, son of Ebiasaph, son of Korah,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>son of Izhar, son of Kohath, son of Levi, son of Israel;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and his brother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10494AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10494AE\"></sup>Asaph, who stood on his right hand, namely, Asaph the son of Berechiah, son of Shimea,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>son of Michael, son of Baaseiah, son of Malchijah,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>son of Ethni, son of Zerah, son of Adaiah,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>son of Ethan, son of Zimmah, son of Shimei,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>son of Jahath, son of Gershom, son of Levi.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>On the left hand were their brothers, the sons of Merari: Ethan the son of Kishi, son of Abdi, son of Malluch,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>son of Hashabiah, son of Amaziah, son of Hilkiah,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>son of Amzi, son of Bani, son of Shemer,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>son of Mahli, son of Mushi, son of Merari, son of Levi.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And their brothers the Levites were appointed for all the service of the tabernacle of the house of God.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>But Aaron and his sons made offerings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10504AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10504AF\"></sup>on the altar of burnt offering and on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10504AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10504AG\"></sup>the altar of incense for all the work of the Most Holy Place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10504AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10504AH\"></sup>to make atonement for Israel, according to all that Moses the servant of God had commanded.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10505AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10505AI\"></sup>These are the sons of Aaron: Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son, Abishua his son,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>These are their dwelling places according to their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10509AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10509AJ\"></sup>settlements within their borders: to the sons of Aaron of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10509AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10509AK\"></sup>clans of Kohathites, for theirs was the first lot,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>to them they gave Hebron in the land of Judah and its surrounding pasturelands,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10511AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10511AL\"></sup>but the fields of the city and its villages they gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10512AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10512AM\"></sup>To the sons of Aaron they gave the cities of refuge: Hebron, Libnah with its pasturelands, Jattir, Eshtemoa with its pasturelands,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Hilen with its pasturelands, Debir with its pasturelands,",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Ashan with its pasturelands, and Beth-shemesh with its pasturelands;",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>and from the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon, Geba with its pasturelands, Alemeth with its pasturelands, and Anathoth with its pasturelands. All their cities throughout their clans were thirteen.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10516AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10516AN\"></sup>To the rest of the Kohathites were given by lot out of the clan of the tribe, out of the half-tribe, the half of Manasseh, ten cities.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>To the Gershomites according to their clans were allotted thirteen cities out of the tribes of Issachar, Asher, Naphtali and Manasseh in Bashan.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10518AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10518AO\"></sup>To the Merarites according to their clans were allotted twelve cities out of the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and Zebulun.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10519AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10519AP\"></sup>So the people of Israel gave the Levites the cities with their pasturelands.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>They gave by lot out of the tribes of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10520AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10520AQ\"></sup>these cities that are mentioned by name.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10521AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10521AR\"></sup>And some of the clans of the sons of Kohath had cities of their territory out of the tribe of Ephraim.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>They were given the cities of refuge: Shechem with its pasturelands in the hill country of Ephraim, Gezer with its pasturelands,",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10523AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10523AS\"></sup>Jokmeam with its pasturelands, Beth-horon with its pasturelands,",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>Aijalon with its pasturelands, Gath-rimmon with its pasturelands,",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>and out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Aner with its pasturelands, and Bileam with its pasturelands, for the rest of the clans of the Kohathites.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10526AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10526AT\"></sup>To the Gershomites were given out of the clan of the half-tribe of Manasseh: Golan in Bashan with its pasturelands and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10526AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10526AU\"></sup>Ashtaroth with its pasturelands;",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>and out of the tribe of Issachar: Kedesh with its pasturelands, Daberath with its pasturelands,",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>Ramoth with its pasturelands, and Anem with its pasturelands;",
			"74": "<sup class=\"versenum\">74 </sup>out of the tribe of Asher: Mashal with its pasturelands, Abdon with its pasturelands,",
			"75": "<sup class=\"versenum\">75 </sup>Hukok with its pasturelands, and Rehob with its pasturelands;",
			"76": "<sup class=\"versenum\">76 </sup>and out of the tribe of Naphtali: Kedesh in Galilee with its pasturelands, Hammon with its pasturelands, and Kiriathaim with its pasturelands.",
			"77": "<sup class=\"versenum\">77 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10532AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10532AV\"></sup>To the rest of the Merarites were allotted out of the tribe of Zebulun: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10532AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10532AW\"></sup>Rimmono with its pasturelands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10532AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10532AX\"></sup>Tabor with its pasturelands,",
			"78": "<sup class=\"versenum\">78 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10533AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10533AY\"></sup>beyond the Jordan at Jericho, on the east side of the Jordan, out of the tribe of Reuben: Bezer in the wilderness with its pasturelands, Jahzah with its pasturelands,",
			"79": "<sup class=\"versenum\">79 </sup>Kedemoth with its pasturelands, and Mephaath with its pasturelands;",
			"80": "<sup class=\"versenum\">80 </sup>and out of the tribe of Gad: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10535AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10535AZ\"></sup>Ramoth in Gilead with its pasturelands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10535BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10535BA\"></sup>Mahanaim with its pasturelands,",
			"81": "<sup class=\"versenum\">81 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10536BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10536BB\"></sup>Heshbon with its pasturelands, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10536BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10536BC\"></sup>Jazer with its pasturelands."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>The sons of Issachar: Tola, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10537A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10537A\"></sup>Puah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10537B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10537B\"></sup>Jashub, and Shimron, four.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The sons of Tola: Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam, and Shemuel, heads of their fathers' houses, namely of Tola, mighty warriors of their generations, their number <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10538C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10538C\"></sup>in the days of David being 22,600.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The son of Uzzi: Izrahiah. And the sons of Izrahiah: Michael, Obadiah, Joel, and Isshiah, all five of them were chief men.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And along with them, by their generations, according to their fathers' houses, were units of the army for war, 36,000, for they had many wives and sons.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Their kinsmen belonging to all the clans of Issachar were in all 87,000 mighty warriors, enrolled by genealogy.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10542D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10542D\"></sup>The sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, and Jediael, three.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Bela: Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri, five, heads of fathers' houses, mighty warriors. And their enrollment by genealogies was 22,034.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Becher: Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth, Abijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10544E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10544E\"></sup>Anathoth, and Alemeth. All these were the sons of Becher.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And their enrollment by genealogies, according to their generations, as heads of their fathers' houses, mighty warriors, was 20,200.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The son of Jediael: Bilhan. And the sons of Bilhan: Jeush, Benjamin, Ehud, Chenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish, and Ahishahar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All these were the sons of Jediael according to the heads of their fathers' houses, mighty warriors, 17,200, able to go to war.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Shuppim and Huppim were the sons of Ir, Hushim the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10548F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10548F\"></sup>Aher.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10549G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10549G\"></sup>The sons of Naphtali: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10549H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10549H\"></sup>Jahziel, Guni, Jezer and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10549I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10549I\"></sup>Shallum, the descendants of Bilhah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10550J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10550J\"></sup>The sons of Manasseh: Asriel, whom his Aramean concubine bore; she bore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10550K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10550K\"></sup>Machir the father of Gilead.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Machir took a wife for Huppim and for Shuppim. The name of his sister was Maacah. And the name of the second was Zelophehad, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10551L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10551L\"></sup>Zelophehad had daughters.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Maacah the wife of Machir bore a son, and she called his name Peresh; and the name of his brother was Sheresh; and his sons were Ulam and Rakem.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The son of Ulam: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10553M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10553M\"></sup>Bedan. These were the sons of Gilead the son of Machir, son of Manasseh.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And his sister Hammolecheth bore Ishhod, Abiezer, and Mahlah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Shemida were Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10556N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10556N\"></sup>sons of Ephraim: Shuthelah, and Bered his son, Tahath his son, Eleadah his son, Tahath his son,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer and Elead, whom the men of Gath who were born in the land killed, because they came down to raid their livestock.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brothers came to comfort him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Ephraim went in to his wife, and she conceived and bore a son. And he called his name Beriah, because disaster had befallen his house.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>His daughter was Sheerah, who built both Lower and Upper <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10560O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10560O\"></sup>Beth-horon, and Uzzen-sheerah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Rephah was his son, Resheph his son, Telah his son, Tahan his son,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ladan his son, Ammihud his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10562P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10562P\"></sup>Elishama his son,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Nun his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10563Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10563Q\"></sup>Joshua his son.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10564R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10564R\"></sup>Their possessions and settlements were Bethel and its towns, and to the east Naaran, and to the west <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10564S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10564S\"></sup>Gezer and its towns, Shechem and its towns, and Ayyah and its towns;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10565T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10565T\"></sup>also in possession of the Manassites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10565U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10565U\"></sup>Beth-shean and its towns, Taanach and its towns, Megiddo and its towns, Dor and its towns. In these lived the sons of Joseph the son of Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10566V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10566V\"></sup>The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, and their sister Serah.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The sons of Beriah: Heber, and Malchiel, who fathered Birzaith.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Heber fathered Japhlet, Shomer, Hotham, and their sister Shua.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The sons of Japhlet: Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath. These are the sons of Japhlet.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The sons of Shemer his brother: Rohgah, Jehubbah, and Aram.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of Helem his brother: Zophah, Imna, Shelesh, and Amal.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The sons of Zophah: Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran, and Beera.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The sons of Jether: Jephunneh, Pispa, and Ara.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Ulla: Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>All of these were men of Asher, heads of fathers' houses, approved, mighty warriors, chiefs of the princes. Their number enrolled by genealogies, for service in war, was 26,000 men."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10577A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10577A\"></sup>Benjamin fathered Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10577B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10577B\"></sup>Aharah the third,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Nohah the fourth, and Rapha the fifth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Bela had sons: Addar, Gera, Abihud,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Abishua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10580C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10580C\"></sup>Naaman, Ahoah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Gera, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10581D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10581D\"></sup>Shephuphan, and Huram.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>These are the sons of Ehud (they were heads of fathers' houses of the inhabitants of Geba, and they were carried into exile to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10582E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10582E\"></sup>Manahath):",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera, that is, Heglam, who fathered Uzza and Ahihud.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Shaharaim fathered sons in the country of Moab after he had sent away Hushim and Baara his wives.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He fathered sons by Hodesh his wife: Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jeuz, Sachia, and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of fathers' houses.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He also fathered sons by Hushim: Abitub and Elpaal.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Elpaal: Eber, Misham, and Shemed, who built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10588F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10588F\"></sup>Ono and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10588G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10588G\"></sup>Lod with its towns,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Beriah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10589H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10589H\"></sup>Shema (they were heads of fathers' houses of the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10589I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10589I\"></sup>Aijalon, who caused the inhabitants of Gath to flee);",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and Ahio, Shashak, and Jeremoth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Zebadiah, Arad, Eder,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Michael, Ishpah, and Joha were sons of Beriah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Ishmerai, Izliah, and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Ishpan, Eber, Eliel,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Abdon, Zichri, Hanan,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Iphdeiah, and Penuel were the sons of Shashak.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zichri were the sons of Jeroham.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>These were the heads of fathers' houses, according to their generations, chief men. These lived in Jerusalem.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10605J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10605J\"></sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10605K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10605K\"></sup>Jeiel the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon, and the name of his wife was Maacah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>His firstborn son: Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Gedor, Ahio, Zecher,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and Mikloth (he fathered Shimeah). Now these also lived opposite their kinsmen in Jerusalem, with their kinsmen.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10609L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10609L\"></sup>Ner was the father of Kish, Kish of Saul, Saul of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10609M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10609M\"></sup>Jonathan, Malchi-shua, Abinadab and Eshbaal;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and the son of Jonathan was Merib-baal; and Merib-baal was the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10610N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10610N\"></sup>Micah.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Ahaz fathered Jehoaddah, and Jehoaddah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri. Zimri fathered Moza.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Moza fathered Binea; Raphah was his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his son.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Azel had six sons, and these are their names: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The sons of Eshek his brother: Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second, and Eliphelet the third.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The sons of Ulam were men who were mighty warriors, bowmen, having many sons and grandsons, 150. All these were Benjaminites."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>So all Israel was recorded in genealogies, and these are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10617A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10617A\"></sup>Judah was taken into exile in Babylon because of their breach of faith.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10618B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10618B\"></sup>Now the first to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10618C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10618C\"></sup>dwell again in their possessions in their cities were Israel, the priests, the Levites, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10618D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10618D\"></sup>temple servants.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And some of the people of Judah, Benjamin, Ephraim, and Manasseh lived in Jerusalem:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Uthai the son of Ammihud, son of Omri, son of Imri, son of Bani, from the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10620E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10620E\"></sup>Perez the son of Judah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And of the Shilonites: Asaiah the firstborn, and his sons.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Of the sons of Zerah: Jeuel and their kinsmen, 690.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Of the Benjaminites: Sallu the son of Meshullam, son of Hodaviah, son of Hassenuah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Ibneiah the son of Jeroham, Elah the son of Uzzi, son of Michri, and Meshullam the son of Shephatiah, son of Reuel, son of Ibnijah;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and their kinsmen according to their generations, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10625F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10625F\"></sup>956. All these were heads of fathers' houses according <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10625G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10625G\"></sup>to their fathers' houses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10626H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10626H\"></sup>Of the priests: Jedaiah, Jehoiarib, Jachin,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Azariah the son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son of Meraioth, son of Ahitub, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10627I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10627I\"></sup>chief officer of the house of God;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, son of Pashhur, son of Malchijah, and Maasai the son of Adiel, son of Jahzerah, son of Meshullam, son of Meshillemith, son of Immer;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>besides their kinsmen, heads of their fathers' houses, 1,760, mighty men for the work of the service of the house of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10630J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10630J\"></sup>Of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam, son of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and Bakbakkar, Heresh, Galal and Mattaniah the son of Mica, son of Zichri, son of Asaph;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun, and Berechiah the son of Asa, son of Elkanah, who lived in the villages of the Netophathites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The gatekeepers were Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman, and their kinsmen (Shallum was the chief);",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>until then they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10634K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10634K\"></sup>in the king's gate on the east side as the gatekeepers of the camps of the Levites.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Shallum the son of Kore, son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10635L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10635L\"></sup>Ebiasaph, son of Korah, and his kinsmen of his fathers' house, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10635M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10635M\"></sup>Korahites, were in charge of the work of the service, keepers of the thresholds of the tent, as their fathers had been in charge of the camp of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, keepers of the entrance.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10636N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10636N\"></sup>Phinehas the son of Eleazar was the chief officer over them in time past; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10637O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10637O\"></sup>Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah was gatekeeper at the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>All these, who were chosen as gatekeepers at the thresholds, were 212. They were enrolled by genealogies in their villages. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10638P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10638P\"></sup>David and Samuel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10638Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10638Q\"></sup>the seer established them in their office of trust.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So they and their sons were in charge of the gates of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that is, the house of the tent, as guards.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The gatekeepers were on the four sides, east, west, north, and south.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And their kinsmen who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10641R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10641R\"></sup>in their villages were obligated to come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10641S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10641S\"></sup>in every seven days, in turn, to be with these,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>for the four chief gatekeepers, who were Levites, were entrusted to be over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10642T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10642T\"></sup>the chambers and the treasures of the house of God.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And they lodged around the house of God, for on them lay the duty of watching, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10643U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10643U\"></sup>they had charge of opening it every morning.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Some of them had charge of the utensils of service, for they were required to count them when they were brought in and taken out.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Others of them were appointed over the furniture and over all the holy utensils, also over the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10645V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10645V\"></sup>fine flour, the wine, the oil, the incense, and the spices.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Others, of the sons of the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10646W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10646W\"></sup>prepared the mixing of the spices,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and Mattithiah, one of the Levites, the firstborn of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10647X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10647X\"></sup>Shallum the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10647Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10647Y\"></sup>Korahite, was entrusted with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10647Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10647Z\"></sup>making the flat cakes.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Also some of their kinsmen of the Kohathites had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10648AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10648AA\"></sup>charge of the showbread, to prepare it every Sabbath.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now these, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10649AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10649AB\"></sup>singers, the heads of fathers' houses of the Levites, were in the chambers of the temple free from other service, for they were on duty day and night.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>These were heads of fathers' houses of the Levites, according to their generations, leaders. These lived in Jerusalem.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10651AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10651AC\"></sup>In Gibeon lived the father of Gibeon, Jeiel, and the name of his wife was Maacah,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and his firstborn son Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah, and Mikloth;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and Mikloth was the father of Shimeam; and these also lived opposite their kinsmen in Jerusalem, with their kinsmen.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10655AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10655AD\"></sup>Ner fathered Kish, Kish fathered Saul, Saul fathered Jonathan, Malchi-shua, Abinadab, and Eshbaal.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And the son of Jonathan was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10656AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10656AE\"></sup>Merib-baal, and Merib-baal fathered Micah.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tahrea, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10657AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10657AF\"></sup>Ahaz.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And Ahaz fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10658AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10658AG\"></sup>Jarah, and Jarah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri. And Zimri fathered Moza.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Moza fathered Binea, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10659AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10659AH\"></sup>Rephaiah was his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his son.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Azel had six sons and these are their names: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan; these were the sons of Azel."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10661A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10661A\"></sup>Now the Philistines fought against Israel, and the men of Israel fled before the Philistines and fell slain on Mount Gilboa.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the Philistines overtook Saul and his sons, and the Philistines struck down Jonathan and Abinadab and Malchi-shua, the sons of Saul.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The battle pressed hard against Saul, and the archers found him, and he was wounded by the archers.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Saul said to his armor-bearer, “Draw your sword and thrust me through with it, lest these uncircumcised come and mistreat me.” But his armor-bearer would not, for he feared greatly. Therefore Saul took his own sword and fell upon it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when his armor-bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell upon his sword and died.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Thus Saul died; he and his three sons and all his house died together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when all the men of Israel who were in the valley saw that the army had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned their cities and fled, and the Philistines came and lived in them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And they stripped him and took his head and his armor, and sent messengers throughout the land of the Philistines to carry the good news to their idols and to the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And they put his armor in the temple of their gods and fastened his head in the temple of Dagon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But when all Jabesh-gilead heard all that the Philistines had done to Saul,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>all the valiant men arose and took away the body of Saul and the bodies of his sons, and brought them to Jabesh. And they buried their bones under the oak in Jabesh and fasted seven days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Saul died <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10673B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10673B\"></sup>for his breach of faith. He broke faith with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in that he did not keep the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10673C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10673C\"></sup>consulted a medium, seeking guidance.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10674D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10674D\"></sup>did not seek guidance from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put him to death and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10674E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10674E\"></sup>turned the kingdom over to David the son of Jesse."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10675A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10675A\"></sup>Then all Israel gathered together to David at Hebron and said, “Behold, we are your bone and flesh.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In times past, even when Saul was king, it was you who led out and brought in Israel. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God said to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10676B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10676B\"></sup>‘You shall be shepherd of my people Israel, and you shall be prince over my people Israel.’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and David made a covenant with them at Hebron before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And they anointed David king over Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10677C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10677C\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Samuel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10678D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10678D\"></sup>that is, Jebus, where the Jebusites were, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10678E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10678E\"></sup>the inhabitants of the land.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The inhabitants of Jebus said to David, “You will not come in here.” Nevertheless, David took the stronghold of Zion, that is, the city of David.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>David said, “Whoever strikes the Jebusites first <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10680F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10680F\"></sup>shall be chief and commander.” And Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first, so he became chief.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And David lived in the stronghold; therefore it was called the city of David.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he built the city all around from the Millo in complete circuit, and Joab repaired the rest of the city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10683G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10683G\"></sup>became greater and greater, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts was with him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10684H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10684H\"></sup>Now these are the chiefs of David's mighty men, who gave him strong support in his kingdom, together with all Israel, to make him king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10684I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10684I\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> concerning Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>This is an account of David's mighty men: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10685J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10685J\"></sup>Jashobeam, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10685K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10685K\"></sup>Hachmonite, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10685L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10685L\"></sup>chief of the three. He wielded his spear against 300 whom he killed at one time.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And next to him among the three mighty men was Eleazar the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10686M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10686M\"></sup>Dodo, the Ahohite.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He was with David at Pas-dammim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10687N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10687N\"></sup>when the Philistines were gathered there for battle. There was a plot of ground full of barley, and the men fled from the Philistines.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But he took his stand in the midst of the plot and defended it and killed the Philistines. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saved them by a great victory.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Three of the thirty chief men went down to the rock to David at the cave of Adullam, when the army of Philistines was encamped in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10689O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10689O\"></sup>Valley of Rephaim.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David was then in the stronghold, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10690P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10690P\"></sup>garrison of the Philistines was then at Bethlehem.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And David said longingly, “Oh that someone would give me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem that is by the gate!”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate and took it and brought it to David. But David would not drink it. He poured it out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and said, “Far be it from me before my God that I should do this. Shall I drink the lifeblood of these men? For at the risk of their lives they brought it.” Therefore he would not drink it. These things did the three mighty men.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now Abishai, the brother of Joab, was chief of the thirty. And he wielded his spear against 300 men and killed them and won a name beside the three.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He was the most renowned of the thirty and became their commander, but he did not attain to the three.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was a valiant man of Kabzeel, a doer of great deeds. He struck down two heroes of Moab. He also went down and struck down a lion in a pit on a day when snow had fallen.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he struck down an Egyptian, a man of great stature, five cubits tall. The Egyptian had in his hand a spear <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10697Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10697Q\"></sup>like a weaver's beam, but Benaiah went down to him with a staff and snatched the spear out of the Egyptian's hand and killed him with his own spear.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada and won a name beside the three mighty men.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He was renowned among the thirty, but he did not attain to the three. And David set him over his bodyguard.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The mighty men were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10700R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10700R\"></sup>Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shammoth of Harod, Helez the Pelonite,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ira the son of Ikkesh of Tekoa, Abiezer of Anathoth,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Maharai of Netophah, Heled the son of Baanah of Netophah,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Ithai the son of Ribai of Gibeah of the people of Benjamin, Benaiah of Pirathon,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Hurai of the brooks of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Azmaveth of Baharum, Eliahba the Shaalbonite,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Hashem the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shagee the Hararite,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Ahiam the son of Sachar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Hezro of Carmel, Naarai the son of Ezbai,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10712S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10712S\"></sup>Hagri,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai of Beeroth, the armor-bearer of Joab the son of Zeruiah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Uriah the Hittite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10715T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10715T\"></sup>Zabad the son of Ahlai,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite, a leader of the Reubenites, and thirty with him,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Hanan the son of Maacah, and Joshaphat the Mithnite,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Jediael the son of Shimri, and Joha his brother, the Tizite,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Eliel the Mahavite, and Jeribai, and Joshaviah, the sons of Elnaam, and Ithmah the Moabite,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Eliel, and Obed, and Jaasiel the Mezobaite."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10722A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10722A\"></sup>Now these are the men who came to David at Ziklag, while he could not move about freely because of Saul the son of Kish. And they were among the mighty men who helped him in war.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10723B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10723B\"></sup>were bowmen and could shoot arrows and sling stones with either the right or the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10723C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10723C\"></sup>left hand; they were Benjaminites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10723D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10723D\"></sup>Saul's kinsmen.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The chief was Ahiezer, then Joash, both sons of Shemaah of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10724E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10724E\"></sup>Gibeah; also Jeziel and Pelet, the sons of Azmaveth; Beracah, Jehu of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10724F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10724F\"></sup>Anathoth,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Ishmaiah of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10725G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10725G\"></sup>Gibeon, a mighty man among the thirty and a leader over the thirty; Jeremiah, Jahaziel, Johanan, Jozabad of Gederah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Eluzai, Jerimoth, Bealiah, Shemariah, Shephatiah the Haruphite;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Elkanah, Isshiah, Azarel, Joezer, and Jashobeam, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10727H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10727H\"></sup>Korahites;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Joelah and Zebadiah, the sons of Jeroham of Gedor.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From the Gadites there went over to David at the stronghold in the wilderness mighty and experienced warriors, expert with shield and spear, whose faces were like the faces of lions and who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10729I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10729I\"></sup>swift as gazelles upon the mountains:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Ezer the chief, Obadiah second, Eliab third,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Mishmannah fourth, Jeremiah fifth,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Attai sixth, Eliel seventh,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Johanan eighth, Elzabad ninth,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jeremiah tenth, Machbannai eleventh.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These Gadites were officers of the army; the least was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10735J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10735J\"></sup>match for a hundred men and the greatest for a thousand.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These are the men who crossed the Jordan in the first month, when it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10736K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10736K\"></sup>overflowing all its banks, and put to flight all those in the valleys, to the east and to the west.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And some of the men of Benjamin and Judah came to the stronghold to David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David went out to meet them and said to them, “If you have come to me in friendship to help me, my heart will be joined to you; but if to betray me to my adversaries, although there is no wrong in my hands, then may the God of our fathers see and rebuke you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10739L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10739L\"></sup>the Spirit clothed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10739M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10739M\"></sup>Amasai, chief of the thirty, and he said,“We are yours, O David,and with you, O son of Jesse!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10739N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10739N\"></sup>Peace, peace to you,and peace to your helpers!For your God helps you.”Then David received them and made them officers of his troops.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Some of the men of Manasseh deserted to David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10740O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10740O\"></sup>when he came with the Philistines for the battle against Saul. (Yet he did not help them, for the rulers of the Philistines took counsel and sent him away, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10740P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10740P\"></sup>“At peril to our heads he will desert to his master Saul.”)",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As he went to Ziklag, these men of Manasseh deserted to him: Adnah, Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu, and Zillethai, chiefs of thousands in Manasseh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They helped David against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10742Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10742Q\"></sup>the band of raiders, for they were all mighty men of valor and were commanders in the army.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For from day to day men came to David to help him, until there was a great army, like an army of God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These are the numbers of the divisions of the armed troops <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10744R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10744R\"></sup>who came to David in Hebron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10744S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10744S\"></sup>to turn the kingdom of Saul over to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10744T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10744T\"></sup>according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The men of Judah bearing shield and spear were 6,800 armed troops.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Of the Simeonites, mighty men of valor for war, 7,100.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Of the Levites 4,600.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The prince Jehoiada, of the house of Aaron, and with him 3,700.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10749U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10749U\"></sup>Zadok, a young man mighty in valor, and twenty-two commanders from his own fathers' house.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Of the Benjaminites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10750V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10750V\"></sup>the kinsmen of Saul, 3,000, of whom the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10750W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10750W\"></sup>majority had to that point kept their allegiance to the house of Saul.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Of the Ephraimites 20,800, mighty men of valor, famous men in their fathers' houses.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Of the half-tribe of Manasseh 18,000, who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10752X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10752X\"></sup>expressly named to come and make David king.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Of Issachar, men who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10753Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10753Y\"></sup>had understanding of the times, to know what Israel ought to do, 200 chiefs, and all their kinsmen under their command.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Of Zebulun 50,000 seasoned troops, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10754Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10754Z\"></sup>equipped for battle with all the weapons of war, to help David with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10754AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10754AA\"></sup>singleness of purpose.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Of Naphtali 1,000 commanders with whom were 37,000 men armed with shield and spear.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Of the Danites 28,600 men equipped for battle.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10757AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10757AB\"></sup>Asher 40,000 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10757AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10757AC\"></sup>seasoned troops <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10757AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10757AD\"></sup>ready for battle.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Of the Reubenites and Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh from beyond the Jordan, 120,000 men armed with all the weapons of war.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>All these, men of war, arrayed in battle order, came to Hebron with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10759AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10759AE\"></sup>a whole heart to make David king over all Israel. Likewise, all the rest of Israel were of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10759AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10759AF\"></sup>single mind to make David king.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And they were there with David for three days, eating and drinking, for their brothers had made preparation for them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And also their relatives, from as far as Issachar and Zebulun and Naphtali, came bringing food on donkeys and on camels and on mules and on oxen, abundant provisions of flour, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10761AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10761AG\"></sup>cakes of figs, clusters of raisins, and wine and oil, oxen and sheep, for there was joy in Israel."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>David consulted with the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, with every leader.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David said to all the assembly of Israel, “If it seems good to you and from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, let us send abroad to our brothers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10763A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10763A\"></sup>who remain in all the lands of Israel, as well as to the priests and Levites in the cities that have pasturelands, that they may be gathered to us.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then let us bring again the ark of our God to us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10764B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10764B\"></sup>for we did not seek it in the days of Saul.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>All the assembly agreed to do so, for the thing was right in the eyes of all the people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10766C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10766C\"></sup>So David assembled all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10766D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10766D\"></sup>from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10766E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10766E\"></sup>Nile of Egypt to Lebo-hamath, to bring the ark of God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10766F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10766F\"></sup>from Kiriath-jearim.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10767G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10767G\"></sup>And David and all Israel went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10767H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10767H\"></sup>Baalah, that is, to Kiriath-jearim that belongs to Judah, to bring up from there the ark of God, which is called by the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10767I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10767I\"></sup>sits enthroned above the cherubim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And they carried the ark of God on a new cart, from the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10768J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10768J\"></sup>Abinadab, and Uzzah and Ahio were driving the cart.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And David and all Israel were celebrating before God with all their might, with song and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10769K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10769K\"></sup>lyres and harps and tambourines and cymbals and trumpets.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And when they came to the threshing floor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10770L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10770L\"></sup>Chidon, Uzzah put out his hand to take hold of the ark, for the oxen stumbled.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Uzzah, and he struck him down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10771M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10771M\"></sup>because he put out his hand to the ark, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10771N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10771N\"></sup>he died there before God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And David was angry because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had broken out against Uzzah. And that place is called Perez-uzza to this day.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And David was afraid of God that day, and he said, “How can I bring the ark of God home to me?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So David did not take the ark home into the city of David, but took it aside to the house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10774O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10774O\"></sup>of Obed-edom the Gittite.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the ark of God remained with the household of Obed-edom in his house three months. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10775P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10775P\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed the household of Obed-edom and all that he had."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10776A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10776A\"></sup>And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, also masons and carpenters to build a house for him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had established him as king over Israel, and that his kingdom was highly exalted for the sake of his people Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And David took more wives in Jerusalem, and David fathered more sons and daughters.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10779B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10779B\"></sup>These are the names of the children born to him in Jerusalem: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10779C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10779C\"></sup>Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Elishama, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10782D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10782D\"></sup>Beeliada and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10782E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10782E\"></sup>Eliphelet.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over all Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. But David heard of it and went out against them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now the Philistines had come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10784F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10784F\"></sup>made a raid in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10784G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10784G\"></sup>Valley of Rephaim.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And David inquired of God, “Shall I go up against the Philistines? Will you give them into my hand?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go up, and I will give them into your hand.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he went up to Baal-perazim, and David struck them down there. And David said, “God has broken through my enemies by my hand, like a bursting flood.” Therefore the name of that place is called Baal-perazim.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they left their gods there, and David gave command, and they were burned.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the Philistines yet again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10788H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10788H\"></sup>made a raid in the valley.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And when David again inquired of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10789I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10789I\"></sup>God said to him, “You shall not go up after them; go around and come against them opposite the balsam trees.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam trees, then go out to battle, for God has gone out before you to strike down the army of the Philistines.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And David did as God commanded him, and they struck down the Philistine army from Gibeon to Gezer.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the fame of David went out into all lands, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10792J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10792J\"></sup>fear of him upon all nations."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>David built houses for himself in the city of David. And he prepared a place for the ark of God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10793A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10793A\"></sup>pitched a tent for it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then David said that no one but the Levites may carry <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10794B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10794B\"></sup>the ark of God, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had chosen them to carry the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to minister to him forever.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10795C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10795C\"></sup>And David assembled all Israel at Jerusalem to bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10795D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10795D\"></sup>to its place, which he had prepared for it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And David gathered together the sons of Aaron and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10796E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10796E\"></sup>the Levites:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>of the sons of Kohath, Uriel the chief, with 120 of his brothers;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>of the sons of Merari, Asaiah the chief, with 220 of his brothers;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>of the sons of Gershom, Joel the chief, with 130 of his brothers;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>of the sons of Elizaphan, Shemaiah the chief, with 200 of his brothers;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>of the sons of Hebron, Eliel the chief, with 80 of his brothers;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>of the sons of Uzziel, Amminadab the chief, with 112 of his brothers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David summoned the priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10803F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10803F\"></sup>Zadok and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10803G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10803G\"></sup>Abiathar, and the Levites Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel, and Amminadab,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and said to them, “You are the heads of the fathers' houses of the Levites. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10804H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10804H\"></sup>Consecrate yourselves, you and your brothers, so that you may bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10804I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10804I\"></sup>to the place that I have prepared for it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10805J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10805J\"></sup>Because you did not carry it the first time, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God broke out against us, because we did not seek him according to the rule.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the priests and the Levites consecrated themselves to bring up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the Levites carried the ark of God on their shoulders <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10807K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10807K\"></sup>with the poles, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10807L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10807L\"></sup>as Moses had commanded according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David also commanded the chiefs of the Levites to appoint their brothers as the singers who should play loudly on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10808M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10808M\"></sup>musical instruments, on harps and lyres and cymbals, to raise sounds of joy.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So the Levites appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10809N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10809N\"></sup>Heman the son of Joel; and of his brothers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10809O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10809O\"></sup>Asaph the son of Berechiah; and of the sons of Merari, their brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10809P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10809P\"></sup>Ethan the son of Kushaiah;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and with them their brothers of the second order, Zechariah, Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, and Mikneiah, and the gatekeepers Obed-edom and Jeiel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan, were to sound bronze cymbals;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Zechariah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10812Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10812Q\"></sup>Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, and Benaiah were to play harps according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10812R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10812R\"></sup>Alamoth;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10813S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10813S\"></sup>Obed-edom, Jeiel, and Azaziah were to lead with lyres according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10813T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10813T\"></sup>the Sheminith.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Chenaniah, leader of the Levites in music, should direct the music, for he understood it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Berechiah and Elkanah were to be gatekeepers for the ark.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah, and Eliezer, the priests, should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10816U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10816U\"></sup>blow the trumpets before the ark of God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10816V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10816V\"></sup>Obed-edom and Jehiah were to be gatekeepers for the ark.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10817W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10817W\"></sup>So David and the elders of Israel and the commanders of thousands went to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10817X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10817X\"></sup>Obed-edom with rejoicing.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And because God helped the Levites who were carrying the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, they sacrificed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10818Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10818Y\"></sup>seven bulls and seven rams.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>David was clothed with a robe of fine linen, as also were all the Levites who were carrying the ark, and the singers and Chenaniah the leader of the music of the singers. And David wore a linen ephod.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So all Israel brought up the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with shouting, to the sound of the horn, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10820Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10820Z\"></sup>trumpets, and cymbals, and made loud music on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10820AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10820AA\"></sup>harps and lyres.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And as the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to the city of David, Michal the daughter of Saul looked out of the window and saw King David dancing and celebrating, and she despised him in her heart."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>And they brought in the ark of God and set it inside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10822A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10822A\"></sup>the tent that David had pitched for it, and they offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And when David had finished offering the burnt offerings and the peace offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and distributed to all Israel, both men and women, to each a loaf of bread, a portion of meat, and a cake of raisins.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then he appointed some of the Levites as ministers before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to invoke, to thank, and to praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10826B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10826B\"></sup>Asaph was the chief, and second to him were Zechariah, Jeiel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, Obed-edom, and Jeiel, who were to play harps and lyres; Asaph was to sound the cymbals,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests were to blow trumpets regularly before the ark of the covenant of God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then on that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10828C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10828C\"></sup>David first appointed that thanksgiving be sung to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by Asaph and his brothers.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10829D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10829D\"></sup>Oh give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10829E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10829E\"></sup>call upon his name;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10829F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10829F\"></sup>make known his deeds among the peoples!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Sing to him, sing praises to him;tell of all his wondrous works!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Glory in his holy name;let the hearts of those who seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rejoice!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10832G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10832G\"></sup>Seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his strength;seek his presence continually!",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10833H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10833H\"></sup>Remember the wondrous works that he has done,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10833I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10833I\"></sup>his miracles and the judgments he uttered,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>O offspring of Israel his servant,children of Jacob, his chosen ones!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10835J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10835J\"></sup>his judgments are in all the earth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Remember his covenant forever,the word that he commanded, for a thousand generations,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the covenant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10837K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10837K\"></sup>that he made with Abraham,his sworn promise to Isaac,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10838L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10838L\"></sup>he confirmed to Jacob as a statute,to Israel as an everlasting covenant,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10839M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10839M\"></sup>“To you I will give the land of Canaan,as your portion for an inheritance.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When you were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10840N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10840N\"></sup>few in number,of little account, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10840O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10840O\"></sup>sojourners in it,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>wandering from nation to nation,from one kingdom to another people,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>he allowed no one to oppress them;he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10842P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10842P\"></sup>rebuked kings on their account,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>saying, “Touch not my anointed ones,do my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10843Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10843Q\"></sup>prophets no harm!”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10844R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10844R\"></sup>Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all the earth!Tell of his salvation from day to day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Declare his glory among the nations,his marvelous works among all the peoples!",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10846S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10846S\"></sup>great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and greatly to be praised,and he is to be feared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10846T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10846T\"></sup>above all gods.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For all the gods of the peoples are worthless idols,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10847U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10847U\"></sup>but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made the heavens.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Splendor and majesty are before him;strength and joy are in his place.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, O families of the peoples,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10849V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10849V\"></sup>ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> glory and strength!",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Ascribe to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the glory due his name;bring an offering and come before him!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10850W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10850W\"></sup>Worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the splendor of holiness;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>tremble before him, all the earth;yes, the world is established; it shall never be moved.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10852X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10852X\"></sup>Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice,and let them say among the nations, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10852Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10852Y\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reigns!”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10853Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10853Z\"></sup>Let the sea roar, and all that fills it;let the field exult, and everything in it!",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then shall the trees of the forest sing for joybefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he comes to judge the earth.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Oh give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is good;for his steadfast love endures forever!",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10856AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10856AA\"></sup>Say also:“Save us, O God of our salvation,and gather and deliver us from among the nations,that we may give thanks to your holy nameand glory in your praise.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10857AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10857AB\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel,from everlasting to everlasting!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10857AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10857AC\"></sup>Then all the people said, “Amen!” and praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So David left Asaph and his brothers there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10858AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10858AD\"></sup>before the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to minister regularly before the ark <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10858AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10858AE\"></sup>as each day required,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10859AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10859AF\"></sup>Obed-edom and his sixty-eight brothers, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10859AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10859AG\"></sup>Obed-edom, the son of Jeduthun, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10859AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10859AH\"></sup>Hosah were to be gatekeepers.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And he left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10860AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10860AI\"></sup>Zadok the priest and his brothers the priests before the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10860AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10860AJ\"></sup>in the high place that was at Gibeon",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>to offer burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10861AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10861AK\"></sup>on the altar of burnt offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10861AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10861AL\"></sup>regularly morning and evening, to do all that is written in the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he commanded Israel.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>With them were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10862AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10862AM\"></sup>Heman and Jeduthun <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10862AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10862AN\"></sup>and the rest of those chosen and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10862AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10862AO\"></sup>expressly named to give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10862AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10862AP\"></sup>for his steadfast love endures forever.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Heman and Jeduthun had trumpets and cymbals for the music and instruments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10863AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10863AQ\"></sup>for sacred song. The sons of Jeduthun were appointed to the gate.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10864AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10864AR\"></sup>Then all the people departed each to his house, and David went home to bless his household."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10865A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10865A\"></sup>Now when David lived in his house, David said to Nathan the prophet, “Behold, I dwell in a house of cedar, but the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is under a tent.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Nathan said to David, “Do all that is in your heart, for God is with you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But that same night the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Nathan,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Go and tell my servant David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10868B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10868B\"></sup>It is not you who will build me a house to dwell in.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For I have not lived in a house since the day I brought up Israel to this day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10869C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10869C\"></sup>but I have gone from tent to tent and from dwelling to dwelling.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In all places where I have moved with all Israel, did I speak a word with any of the judges of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd my people, saying, “Why have you not built me a house of cedar?”’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now, therefore, thus shall you say to my servant David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, I took you from the pasture, from following the sheep, to be prince over my people Israel,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and I have been with you wherever you have gone and have cut off all your enemies from before you. And I will make for you a name, like the name of the great ones of the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And I will appoint a place for my people Israel and will plant them, that they may dwell in their own place and be disturbed no more. And violent men shall waste them no more, as formerly,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>from the time that I appointed judges over my people Israel. And I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10874D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10874D\"></sup>will subdue all your enemies. Moreover, I declare to you that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will build you a house.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When your days are fulfilled to walk with your fathers, I will raise up your offspring after you, one of your own sons, and I will establish his kingdom.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He shall build a house for me, and I will establish his throne forever.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10877E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10877E\"></sup>I will be to him a father, and he shall be to me a son. I will not take my steadfast love from him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10877F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10877F\"></sup>as I took it from him who was before you,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>but I will confirm him in my house and in my kingdom forever, and his throne shall be established forever.’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In accordance with all these words, and in accordance with all this vision, Nathan spoke to David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then King David went in and sat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “Who am I, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, and what is my house, that you have brought me thus far?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And this was a small thing in your eyes, O God. You have also spoken of your servant's house for a great while to come, and have shown me future generations, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And what more can David say to you for honoring your servant? For you know your servant.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10883G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10883G\"></sup>For your servant's sake, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and according to your own heart, you have done all this greatness, in making known all these great things.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There is none like you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and there is no God besides you, according to all that we have heard with our ears.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And who is like your people Israel, the one nation on earth whom God went to redeem to be his people, making for yourself a name for great and awesome things, in driving out nations before your people whom you redeemed from Egypt?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And you made your people Israel to be your people forever, and you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, became their God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, let the word that you have spoken concerning your servant and concerning his house be established forever, and do as you have spoken,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and your name will be established and magnified forever, saying, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, the God of Israel, is Israel's God,’ and the house of your servant David will be established before you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For you, my God, have revealed to your servant that you will build a house for him. Therefore your servant has found courage to pray before you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you are God, and you have promised this good thing to your servant.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now you have been pleased to bless the house of your servant, that it may continue forever before you, for it is you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who have blessed, and it is blessed forever.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10892A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10892A\"></sup>After this David defeated the Philistines and subdued them, and he took Gath and its villages out of the hand of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he defeated Moab, and the Moabites became servants to David and brought tribute.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David also defeated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10894B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10894B\"></sup>Hadadezer king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10894C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10894C\"></sup>Zobah-Hamath, as he went to set up his monument at the river Euphrates.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And David took from him 1,000 chariots, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10895D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10895D\"></sup>7,000 horsemen, and 20,000 foot soldiers. And David hamstrung all the chariot horses, but left enough for 100 chariots.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10896E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10896E\"></sup>of Zobah, David struck down 22,000 men of the Syrians.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus, and the Syrians became servants to David and brought tribute. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave victory to David wherever he went.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And David took the shields of gold that were carried by the servants of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10899F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10899F\"></sup>Tibhath and from Cun, cities of Hadadezer, David took a large amount of bronze. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10899G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10899G\"></sup>With it Solomon made the bronze sea and the pillars and the vessels of bronze.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10900H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10900H\"></sup>Tou king of Hamath heard that David had defeated the whole army of Hadadezer, king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10900I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10900I\"></sup>of Zobah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>he sent his son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10901J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10901J\"></sup>Hadoram to King David, to ask about his health and to bless him because he had fought against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10901K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10901K\"></sup>Hadadezer and defeated him; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10901L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10901L\"></sup>Hadadezer had often been at war with Tou. And he sent all sorts of articles of gold, of silver, and of bronze.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>These also King David dedicated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, together with the silver and gold that he had carried off from all the nations, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10902M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10902M\"></sup>Edom, Moab, the Ammonites, the Philistines, and Amalek.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10903N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10903N\"></sup>Abishai, the son of Zeruiah, killed 18,000 Edomites in the Valley of Salt.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then he put garrisons in Edom, and all the Edomites became David's servants. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave victory to David wherever he went.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So David reigned over all Israel, and he administered justice and equity to all his people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10906O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10906O\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army; and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10907P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10907P\"></sup>and Zadok the son of Ahitub and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10907Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10907Q\"></sup>Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were priests; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10907R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10907R\"></sup>Shavsha was secretary;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and David's sons were the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10908S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10908S\"></sup>chief officials in the service of the king."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10909A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10909A\"></sup>Now after this Nahash the king of the Ammonites died, and his son reigned in his place.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David said, “I will deal kindly with Hanun the son of Nahash, for his father dealt kindly with me.” So David sent messengers to console him concerning his father. And David's servants came to the land of the Ammonites to Hanun to console him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the princes of the Ammonites said to Hanun, “Do you think, because David has sent comforters to you, that he is honoring your father? Have not his servants come to you to search and to overthrow and to spy out the land?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Hanun took David's servants and shaved them and cut off their garments in the middle, at their hips, and sent them away;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and they departed. When David was told concerning the men, he sent messengers to meet them, for the men were greatly ashamed. And the king said, “Remain at Jericho until your beards have grown and then return.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the Ammonites saw that they had become a stench to David, Hanun and the Ammonites sent 1,000 talents of silver to hire chariots and horsemen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10914B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10914B\"></sup>from Mesopotamia, from Aram-maacah, and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10914C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10914C\"></sup>Zobah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They hired 32,000 chariots and the king of Maacah with his army, who came and encamped before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10915D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10915D\"></sup>Medeba. And the Ammonites were mustered from their cities and came to battle.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When David heard of it, he sent Joab and all the army of the mighty men.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the Ammonites came out and drew up in battle array at the entrance of the city, and the kings who had come were by themselves in the open country.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Joab saw that the battle was set against him both in front and in the rear, he chose some of the best men of Israel and arrayed them against the Syrians.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The rest of his men he put in the charge of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10919E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10919E\"></sup>Abishai his brother, and they were arrayed against the Ammonites.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he said, “If the Syrians are too strong for me, then you shall help me, but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will help you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Be strong, and let us use our strength for our people and for the cities of our God, and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> do what seems good to him.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Joab and the people who were with him drew near before the Syrians for battle, and they fled before him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when the Ammonites saw that the Syrians fled, they likewise fled before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10923F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10923F\"></sup>Abishai, Joab's brother, and entered the city. Then Joab came to Jerusalem.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But when the Syrians saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they sent messengers and brought out the Syrians who were beyond the Euphrates, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10924G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10924G\"></sup>Shophach the commander of the army of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10924H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10924H\"></sup>Hadadezer at their head.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And when it was told to David, he gathered all Israel together and crossed the Jordan and came to them and drew up his forces against them. And when David set the battle in array against the Syrians, they fought with him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the Syrians fled before Israel, and David killed of the Syrians the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10926I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10926I\"></sup>7,000 chariots and 40,000 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10926J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10926J\"></sup>foot soldiers, and put to death also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10926K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10926K\"></sup>Shophach the commander of their army.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And when the servants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10927L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10927L\"></sup>Hadadezer saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they made peace with David and became subject to him. So the Syrians were not willing to save the Ammonites anymore."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10928A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10928A\"></sup>In the spring of the year, the time when kings go out to battle, Joab led out the army and ravaged the country of the Ammonites and came and besieged Rabbah. But David remained at Jerusalem. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10928B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10928B\"></sup>Joab struck down Rabbah and overthrew it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10929C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10929C\"></sup>And David took the crown of their king from his head. He found that it weighed a talent of gold, and in it was a precious stone. And it was placed on David's head. And he brought out the spoil of the city, a very great amount.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he brought out the people who were in it and set them to labor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10930D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10930D\"></sup>with saws and iron picks and axes. And thus David did to all the cities of the Ammonites. Then David and all the people returned to Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10931E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10931E\"></sup>And after this there arose war with the Philistines at Gezer. Then Sibbecai the Hushathite struck down Sippai, who was one of the descendants of the giants, and the Philistines were subdued.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And there was again war with the Philistines, and Elhanan the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10932F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10932F\"></sup>Jair struck down Lahmi <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10932G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10932G\"></sup>the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the shaft of whose spear was like a weaver's beam.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And there was again war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature, who had six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four in number, and he also was descended from the giants.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when he taunted Israel, Jonathan the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10934H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10934H\"></sup>Shimea, David's brother, struck him down.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These were descended from the giants in Gath, and they fell by the hand of David and by the hand of his servants."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10936A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10936A\"></sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10936B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10936B\"></sup>Satan stood against Israel and incited David to number Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David said to Joab and the commanders of the army, “Go, number Israel, from Beersheba to Dan, and bring me a report, that I may know their number.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Joab said, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> add to his people a hundred times as many as they are! Are they not, my lord the king, all of them my lord's servants? Why then should my lord require this? Why should it be a cause of guilt for Israel?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the king's word prevailed against Joab. So Joab departed and went throughout all Israel and came back to Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Joab gave the sum of the numbering of the people to David. In all Israel there were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10940C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10940C\"></sup>1,100,000 men who drew the sword, and in Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10940D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10940D\"></sup>470,000 who drew the sword.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10941E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10941E\"></sup>But he did not include Levi and Benjamin in the numbering, for the king's command was abhorrent to Joab.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But God was displeased with this thing, and he struck Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And David said to God, “I have sinned greatly in that I have done this thing. But now, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10943F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10943F\"></sup>take away the iniquity of your servant, for I have acted very foolishly.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Gad, David's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10944G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10944G\"></sup>seer, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Go and say to David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Three things I offer you; choose one of them, that I may do it to you.’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Gad came to David and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Choose what you will:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>either <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10947H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10947H\"></sup>three years of famine, or three months of devastation by your foes while the sword of your enemies overtakes you, or else three days of the sword of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, pestilence on the land, with the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroying throughout all the territory of Israel.’ Now decide what answer I shall return to him who sent me.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then David said to Gad, “I am in great distress. Let me fall into the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for his mercy is very great, but do not let me fall into the hand of man.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a pestilence on Israel, and 70,000 men of Israel fell.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And God sent the angel to Jerusalem to destroy it, but as he was about to destroy it, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10950I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10950I\"></sup>relented from the calamity. And he said to the angel who was working destruction, “It is enough; now stay your hand.” And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was standing by the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And David lifted his eyes and saw the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> standing between earth and heaven, and in his hand a drawn sword stretched out over Jerusalem. Then David and the elders, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10951J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10951J\"></sup>clothed in sackcloth, fell upon their faces.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And David said to God, “Was it not I who gave command to number the people? It is I who have sinned and done great evil. But these sheep, what have they done? Please let your hand, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, be against me and against my father's house. But do not let the plague be on your people.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10953K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10953K\"></sup>the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Gad to say to David that David should go up and raise an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So David went up at Gad's word, which he had spoken in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now Ornan was threshing wheat. He turned and saw the angel, and his four sons who were with him hid themselves.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As David came to Ornan, Ornan looked and saw David and went out from the threshing floor and paid homage to David with his face to the ground.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And David said to Ornan, “Give me the site of the threshing floor that I may build on it an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—give it to me at its full price—that the plague may be averted from the people.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Ornan said to David, “Take it, and let my lord the king do what seems good to him. See, I give the oxen for burnt offerings and the threshing sledges for the wood and the wheat for a grain offering; I give it all.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But King David said to Ornan, “No, but I will buy them for the full price. I will not take for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> what is yours, nor offer burnt offerings that cost me nothing.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So David paid Ornan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10960L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10960L\"></sup>600 shekels of gold by weight for the site.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And David built there an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and presented burnt offerings and peace offerings and called on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10961M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10961M\"></sup>answered him with fire from heaven upon the altar of burnt offering.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded the angel, and he put his sword back into its sheath.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>At that time, when David saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had answered him at the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite, he sacrificed there.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which Moses had made in the wilderness, and the altar of burnt offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10964N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10964N\"></sup>were at that time in the high place at Gibeon,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but David could not go before it to inquire of God, for he was afraid of the sword of the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Then David said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10966A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10966A\"></sup>“Here shall be the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God and here the altar of burnt offering for Israel.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David commanded to gather together the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10967B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10967B\"></sup>resident aliens who were in the land of Israel, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10967C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10967C\"></sup>set stonecutters to prepare dressed stones for building the house of God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David also provided great quantities of iron for nails for the doors of the gates and for clamps, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10968D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10968D\"></sup>as well as bronze in quantities beyond weighing,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and cedar timbers without number, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10969E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10969E\"></sup>for the Sidonians and Tyrians brought great quantities of cedar to David.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For David said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10970F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10970F\"></sup>“Solomon my son is young and inexperienced, and the house that is to be built for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> must be exceedingly magnificent, of fame and glory throughout all lands. I will therefore make preparation for it.” So David provided materials in great quantity before his death.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he called for Solomon his son and charged him to build a house for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David said to Solomon, “My son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10972G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10972G\"></sup>I had it in my heart to build a house to the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to me, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10973H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10973H\"></sup>‘You have shed much blood and have waged great wars. You shall not build a house to my name, because you have shed so much blood before me on the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Behold, a son shall be born to you who shall be a man of rest. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10974I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10974I\"></sup>I will give him rest from all his surrounding enemies. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10974J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10974J\"></sup>For his name shall be Solomon, and I will give peace and quiet to Israel in his days.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10975K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10975K\"></sup>He shall build a house for my name. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10975L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10975L\"></sup>He shall be my son, and I will be his father, and I will establish his royal throne in Israel forever.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Now, my son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10976M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10976M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you, so that you may succeed in building the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, as he has spoken concerning you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10977N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10977N\"></sup>Only, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> grant you discretion and understanding, that when he gives you charge over Israel you may keep the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10978O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10978O\"></sup>Then you will prosper if you are careful to observe the statutes and the rules that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses for Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10978P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10978P\"></sup>Be strong and courageous. Fear not; do not be dismayed.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>With great pains I have provided for the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10979Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10979Q\"></sup>100,000 talents of gold, a million talents of silver, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10979R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10979R\"></sup>bronze and iron beyond weighing, for there is so much of it; timber and stone, too, I have provided. To these you must add.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You have an abundance of workmen: stonecutters, masons, carpenters, and all kinds of craftsmen without number, skilled in working",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>gold, silver, bronze, and iron. Arise and work! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10981S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10981S\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>David also commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10982T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10982T\"></sup>all the leaders of Israel to help Solomon his son, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Is not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God with you? And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10983U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10983U\"></sup>has he not given you peace on every side? For he has delivered the inhabitants of the land into my hand, and the land is subdued before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10984V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10984V\"></sup>set your mind and heart to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. Arise and build the sanctuary of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10984W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10984W\"></sup>so that the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the holy vessels of God may be brought into a house built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10984X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10984X\"></sup>for the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10985A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10985A\"></sup>When David was old and full of days, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10985B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10985B\"></sup>he made Solomon his son king over Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David assembled all the leaders of Israel and the priests and the Levites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10987C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10987C\"></sup>thirty years old and upward, were numbered, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10987D\"></sup>the total was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10987E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10987E\"></sup>38,000 men.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Twenty-four thousand of these,” David said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10988F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10988F\"></sup>“shall have charge of the work in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, 6,000 shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10988G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10988G\"></sup>officers and judges,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>4,000 gatekeepers, and 4,000 shall offer praises to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the instruments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10989H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10989H\"></sup>that I have made for praise.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10990I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10990I\"></sup>And David organized them in divisions <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10990J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10990J\"></sup>corresponding to the sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10991K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10991K\"></sup>The sons of Gershon were Ladan and Shimei.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Ladan: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10992L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10992L\"></sup>Jehiel the chief, and Zetham, and Joel, three.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Shimei: Shelomoth, Haziel, and Haran, three. These were the heads of the fathers' houses of Ladan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the sons of Shimei: Jahath, Zina, and Jeush and Beriah. These four were the sons of Shimei.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jahath was the chief, and Zizah the second; but Jeush and Beriah did not have many sons, therefore they became counted as a single father's house.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10996M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10996M\"></sup>The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, four.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10997N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10997N\"></sup>The sons of Amram: Aaron and Moses. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10997O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10997O\"></sup>Aaron was set apart to dedicate the most holy things, that he and his sons forever should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10997P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10997P\"></sup>make offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10997Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10997Q\"></sup>minister to him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10997R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10997R\"></sup>pronounce blessings in his name forever.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But the sons of Moses the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10998S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10998S\"></sup>man of God were named among the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10998T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10998T\"></sup>tribe of Levi.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-10999U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-10999U\"></sup>sons of Moses: Gershom and Eliezer.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Gershom: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11000V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11000V\"></sup>Shebuel the chief.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Eliezer: Rehabiah the chief. Eliezer had no other sons, but the sons of Rehabiah were very many.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Izhar: Shelomith the chief.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11003W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11003W\"></sup>sons of Hebron: Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, and Jekameam the fourth.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11004X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11004X\"></sup>The sons of Uzziel: Micah the chief and Isshiah the second.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11005Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11005Y\"></sup>The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli: Eleazar and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11005Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11005Z\"></sup>Kish.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Eleazar died <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11006AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11006AA\"></sup>having no sons, but only daughters; their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11006AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11006AB\"></sup>kinsmen, the sons of Kish, married them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11007AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11007AC\"></sup>The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jeremoth, three.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11008AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11008AD\"></sup>These were the sons of Levi by their fathers' houses, the heads of fathers' houses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11008AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11008AE\"></sup>as they were listed according to the number of the names of the individuals from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11008AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11008AF\"></sup>twenty years old and upward who were to do the work for the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For David said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11009AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11009AG\"></sup>has given rest to his people, and he dwells in Jerusalem forever.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And so the Levites no longer need <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11010AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11010AH\"></sup>to carry the tabernacle or any of the things for its service.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For by the last words of David the sons of Levi were numbered from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11011AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11011AI\"></sup>twenty years old and upward.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For their duty was to assist the sons of Aaron for the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, having the care of the courts and the chambers, the cleansing of all that is holy, and any work for the service of the house of God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Their duty was also to assist with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11013AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11013AJ\"></sup>showbread, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11013AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11013AK\"></sup>flour for the grain offering, the wafers of unleavened bread, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11013AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11013AL\"></sup>baked offering, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11013AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11013AM\"></sup>offering mixed with oil, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11013AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11013AN\"></sup>measures of quantity or size.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And they were to stand every morning, thanking and praising the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and likewise at evening,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and whenever burnt offerings were offered to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11015AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11015AO\"></sup>on Sabbaths, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11015AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11015AP\"></sup>new moons, and feast days, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11015AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11015AQ\"></sup>according to the number required of them, regularly before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11016AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11016AR\"></sup>they were to keep charge of the tent of meeting and the sanctuary, and to attend the sons of Aaron, their brothers, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11016AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11016AS\"></sup>service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>The divisions of the sons of Aaron were these. The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11017A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11017A\"></sup>Aaron: Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11018B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11018B\"></sup>But Nadab and Abihu died before their father and had no children, so Eleazar and Ithamar became the priests.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>With the help of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11019C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11019C\"></sup>Zadok of the sons of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, David organized them according to the appointed duties in their service.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Since more chief men were found among the sons of Eleazar than among the sons of Ithamar, they organized them under sixteen heads of fathers' houses of the sons of Eleazar, and eight of the sons of Ithamar.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They divided them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11021D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11021D\"></sup>by lot, all alike, for there were sacred officers and officers of God among both the sons of Eleazar and the sons of Ithamar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the scribe Shemaiah, the son of Nethanel, a Levite, recorded them in the presence of the king and the princes and Zadok the priest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11022E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11022E\"></sup>Ahimelech the son of Abiathar and the heads of the fathers' houses of the priests and of the Levites, one father's house being chosen for Eleazar and one chosen for Ithamar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The first lot fell to Jehoiarib, the second to Jedaiah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>the fifth to Malchijah, the sixth to Mijamin,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11026F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11026F\"></sup>Abijah,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the ninth to Jeshua, the tenth to Shecaniah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Jeshebeab,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Happizzez,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Jehezkel,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the twenty-first to Jachin, the twenty-second to Gamul,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the twenty-third to Delaiah, the twenty-fourth to Maaziah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These had as their appointed duty in their service <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11035G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11035G\"></sup>to come into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> according to the procedure established for them by Aaron their father, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel had commanded him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And of the rest of the sons of Levi: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11036H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11036H\"></sup>of the sons of Amram, Shubael; of the sons of Shubael, Jehdeiah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11037I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11037I\"></sup>Of Rehabiah: of the sons of Rehabiah, Isshiah the chief.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Of the Izharites, Shelomoth; of the sons of Shelomoth, Jahath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11039J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11039J\"></sup>The sons of Hebron: Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, Jekameam the fourth.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11040K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11040K\"></sup>The sons of Uzziel, Micah; of the sons of Micah, Shamir.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The brother of Micah, Isshiah; of the sons of Isshiah, Zechariah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11042L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11042L\"></sup>The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Jaaziah: Beno.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Merari: of Jaaziah, Beno, Shoham, Zaccur, and Ibri.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Of Mahli: Eleazar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11044M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11044M\"></sup>who had no sons.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Of Kish, the sons of Kish: Jerahmeel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11046N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11046N\"></sup>The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jerimoth. These were the sons of the Levites according to their fathers' houses.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These also, the head of each father's house and his younger brother alike, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11047O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11047O\"></sup>cast lots, just as their brothers the sons of Aaron, in the presence of King David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11047P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11047P\"></sup>Zadok, Ahimelech, and the heads of fathers' houses of the priests and of the Levites."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>David and the chiefs of the service also set apart for the service the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11048A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11048A\"></sup>Asaph, and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11048B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11048B\"></sup>Heman, and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11048C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11048C\"></sup>Jeduthun, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11048D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11048D\"></sup>prophesied with lyres, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11048E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11048E\"></sup>harps, and with cymbals. The list of those who did the work and of their duties was:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Of the sons of Asaph: Zaccur, Joseph, Nethaniah, and Asharelah, sons of Asaph, under the direction of Asaph, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11049F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11049F\"></sup>prophesied under the direction of the king.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Of Jeduthun, the sons of Jeduthun: Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the direction of their father Jeduthun, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11050G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11050G\"></sup>who prophesied with the lyre in thanksgiving and praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Of Heman, the sons of Heman: Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, and Romamti-ezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, Mahazioth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All these were the sons of Heman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11052H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11052H\"></sup>the king's seer, according to the promise of God to exalt him, for God had given Heman fourteen sons and three daughters.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They were all under the direction of their father in the music in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with cymbals, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11053I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11053I\"></sup>harps, and lyres for the service of the house of God. Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman were under the order of the king.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The number of them along with their brothers, who were trained in singing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all who were skillful, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11054J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11054J\"></sup>288.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And they cast lots for their duties, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11055K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11055K\"></sup>small and great, teacher and pupil alike.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The first lot fell for Asaph to Joseph; the second to Gedaliah, to him and his brothers and his sons, twelve;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the third to Zaccur, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the fourth to Izri, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the fifth to Nethaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the sixth to Bukkiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the seventh to Jesharelah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the eighth to Jeshaiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the ninth to Mattaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the tenth to Shimei, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the eleventh to Azarel, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the twelfth to Hashabiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>to the thirteenth, Shubael, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>to the fourteenth, Mattithiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>to the fifteenth, to Jeremoth, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>to the sixteenth, to Hananiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>to the seventeenth, to Joshbekashah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>to the eighteenth, to Hanani, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>to the nineteenth, to Mallothi, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>to the twentieth, to Eliathah, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>to the twenty-first, to Hothir, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>to the twenty-second, to Giddalti, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>to the twenty-third, to Mahazioth, his sons and his brothers, twelve;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>to the twenty-fourth, to Romamti-ezer, his sons and his brothers, twelve."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>As for the divisions of the gatekeepers: of the Korahites, Meshelemiah the son of Kore, of the sons of Asaph.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Meshelemiah had sons: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11080A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11080A\"></sup>Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second, Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elam the fifth, Jehohanan the sixth, Eliehoenai the seventh.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11082B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11082B\"></sup>Obed-edom had sons: Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second, Joah the third, Sachar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Peullethai the eighth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11083C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11083C\"></sup>for God blessed him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Also to his son Shemaiah were sons born who were rulers in their fathers' houses, for they were men of great ability.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Shemaiah: Othni, Rephael, Obed and Elzabad, whose brothers were able men, Elihu and Semachiah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All these were of the sons of Obed-edom with their sons and brothers, able men qualified for the service; sixty-two of Obed-edom.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Meshelemiah had sons and brothers, able men, eighteen.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11088D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11088D\"></sup>Hosah, of the sons of Merari, had sons: Shimri the chief (for though he was not the firstborn, his father made him chief),",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, Zechariah the fourth: all the sons and brothers of Hosah were thirteen.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>These divisions of the gatekeepers, corresponding to their chief men, had duties, just as their brothers did, ministering in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they cast lots by fathers' houses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11091E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11091E\"></sup>small and great alike, for their gates.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The lot for the east fell to Shelemiah. They cast lots also for his son Zechariah, a shrewd counselor, and his lot came out for the north.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Obed-edom's came out for the south, and to his sons was allotted <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11093F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11093F\"></sup>the gatehouse.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For Shuppim and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11094G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11094G\"></sup>Hosah it came out for the west, at the gate of Shallecheth on the road that goes up. Watch corresponded to watch.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>On the east there were six each day, on the north four each day, on the south four each day, as well as two and two at the gatehouse.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11096H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11096H\"></sup>colonnade on the west there were four at the road and two at the colonnade.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These were the divisions of the gatekeepers among the Korahites and the sons of Merari.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And of the Levites, Ahijah had charge of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11098I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11098I\"></sup>the treasuries of the house of God and the treasuries of the dedicated gifts.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Ladan, the sons of the Gershonites belonging to Ladan, the heads of the fathers' houses belonging to Ladan the Gershonite: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11099J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11099J\"></sup>Jehieli.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11100K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11100K\"></sup>The sons of Jehieli, Zetham, and Joel his brother, were in charge of the treasuries of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11101L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11101L\"></sup>Of the Amramites, the Izharites, the Hebronites, and the Uzzielites—",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11102M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11102M\"></sup>Shebuel the son of Gershom, son of Moses, was chief officer in charge of the treasuries.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>His brothers: from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11103N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11103N\"></sup>Eliezer were his son Rehabiah, and his son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11103O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11103O\"></sup>Jeshaiah, and his son Joram, and his son Zichri, and his son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11103P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11103P\"></sup>Shelomoth.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>This Shelomoth and his brothers were in charge of all the treasuries of the dedicated gifts that David the king and the heads of the fathers' houses and the officers of the thousands and the hundreds and the commanders of the army <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11104Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11104Q\"></sup>had dedicated.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>From spoil won in battles they dedicated gifts for the maintenance of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Also all that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11106R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11106R\"></sup>Samuel the seer and Saul the son of Kish and Abner the son of Ner and Joab the son of Zeruiah had dedicated—all dedicated gifts were in the care of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11106S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11106S\"></sup>Shelomoth and his brothers.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Of the Izharites, Chenaniah and his sons were appointed to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11107T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11107T\"></sup>external duties for Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11107U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11107U\"></sup>as officers and judges.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Of the Hebronites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11108V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11108V\"></sup>Hashabiah and his brothers, 1,700 men of ability, had the oversight of Israel westward of the Jordan for all the work of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the service of the king.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Of the Hebronites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11109W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11109W\"></sup>Jerijah was chief of the Hebronites of whatever genealogy or fathers' houses. (In the fortieth year of David's reign search was made and men of great ability among them were found at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11109X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11109X\"></sup>Jazer in Gilead.)",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>King David appointed him and his brothers, 2,700 men of ability, heads of fathers' houses, to have the oversight of the Reubenites, the Gadites and the half-tribe of the Manassites for everything pertaining to God and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11110Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11110Y\"></sup>the affairs of the king."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>This is the number of the people of Israel, the heads of fathers' houses, the commanders of thousands and hundreds, and their officers who served the king in all matters concerning the divisions that came and went, month after month throughout the year, each division numbering 24,000:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11112A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11112A\"></sup>Jashobeam the son of Zabdiel was in charge of the first division in the first month; in his division were 24,000.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11113B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11113B\"></sup>descendant of Perez and was chief of all the commanders. He served for the first month.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11114C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11114C\"></sup>Dodai the Ahohite was in charge of the division of the second month; in his division were 24,000.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The third commander, for the third month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11115D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11115D\"></sup>Benaiah, the son of Jehoiada the chief priest; in his division were 24,000.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>This is the Benaiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11116E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11116E\"></sup>who was a mighty man of the thirty and in command of the thirty; Ammizabad his son was in charge of his division.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11117F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11117F\"></sup>Asahel the brother of Joab was fourth, for the fourth month, and his son Zebadiah after him; in his division were 24,000.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The fifth commander, for the fifth month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11118G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11118G\"></sup>Shamhuth the Izrahite; in his division were 24,000.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Sixth, for the sixth month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11119H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11119H\"></sup>Ira, the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite; in his division were 24,000.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Seventh, for the seventh month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11120I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11120I\"></sup>Helez the Pelonite, of the sons of Ephraim; in his division were 24,000.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Eighth, for the eighth month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11121J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11121J\"></sup>Sibbecai the Hushathite, of the Zerahites; in his division were 24,000.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Ninth, for the ninth month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11122K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11122K\"></sup>Abiezer of Anathoth, a Benjaminite; in his division were 24,000.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Tenth, for the tenth month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11123L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11123L\"></sup>Maharai of Netophah, of the Zerahites; in his division were 24,000.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Eleventh, for the eleventh month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11124M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11124M\"></sup>Benaiah of Pirathon, of the sons of Ephraim; in his division were 24,000.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Twelfth, for the twelfth month, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11125N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11125N\"></sup>Heldai the Netophathite, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11125O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11125O\"></sup>Othniel; in his division were 24,000.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Over the tribes of Israel, for the Reubenites, Eliezer the son of Zichri was chief officer; for the Simeonites, Shephatiah the son of Maacah;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>for Levi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11127P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11127P\"></sup>Hashabiah the son of Kemuel; for Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11127Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11127Q\"></sup>Zadok;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>for Judah, Elihu, one of David's brothers; for Issachar, Omri the son of Michael;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>for Zebulun, Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah; for Naphtali, Jeremoth the son of Azriel;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>for the Ephraimites, Hoshea the son of Azaziah; for the half-tribe of Manasseh, Joel the son of Pedaiah;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>for the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead, Iddo the son of Zechariah; for Benjamin, Jaasiel the son of Abner;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for Dan, Azarel the son of Jeroham. These were the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11132R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11132R\"></sup>leaders of the tribes of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>David did not count those below twenty years of age, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11133S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11133S\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had promised to make Israel as many as the stars of heaven.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah began to count, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11134T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11134T\"></sup>did not finish. Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11134U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11134U\"></sup>wrath came upon Israel for this, and the number was not entered in the chronicles of King David.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Over the king's treasuries was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11135V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11135V\"></sup>Azmaveth the son of Adiel; and over the treasuries in the country, in the cities, in the villages, and in the towers, was Jonathan the son of Uzziah;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and over those who did the work of the field for tilling the soil was Ezri the son of Chelub;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and over the vineyards was Shimei the Ramathite; and over the produce of the vineyards for the wine cellars was Zabdi the Shiphmite.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Over the olive and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11138W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11138W\"></sup>sycamore trees in the Shephelah was Baal-hanan the Gederite; and over the stores of oil was Joash.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Over the herds that pastured in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11139X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11139X\"></sup>Sharon was Shitrai the Sharonite; over the herds in the valleys was Shaphat the son of Adlai.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Over the camels was Obil the Ishmaelite; and over the donkeys was Jehdeiah the Meronothite. Over the flocks was Jaziz the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11140Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11140Y\"></sup>Hagrite.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>All these were stewards of King David's property.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Jonathan, David's uncle, was a counselor, being a man of understanding and a scribe. He and Jehiel the son of Hachmoni attended the king's sons.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11143Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11143Z\"></sup>Ahithophel was the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11143AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11143AA\"></sup>king's counselor, and Hushai the Archite was the king's friend.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Ahithophel was succeeded by Jehoiada the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11144AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11144AB\"></sup>Benaiah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11144AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11144AC\"></sup>Abiathar. Joab was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11144AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11144AD\"></sup>commander of the king's army."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11145A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11145A\"></sup>David assembled at Jerusalem all the officials of Israel, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11145B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11145B\"></sup>officials of the tribes, the officers of the divisions that served the king, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11145C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11145C\"></sup>commanders of thousands, the commanders of hundreds, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11145D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11145D\"></sup>stewards of all the property and livestock of the king and his sons, together with the palace officials, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11145E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11145E\"></sup>mighty men and all the seasoned warriors.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then King David rose to his feet and said: “Hear me, my brothers and my people. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11146F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11146F\"></sup>I had it in my heart to build a house of rest for the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11146G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11146G\"></sup>footstool of our God, and I made preparations for building.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But God said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11147H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11147H\"></sup>‘You may not build a house for my name, for you are a man of war and have shed blood.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Yet the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11148I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11148I\"></sup>chose me from all my father's house to be king over Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11148J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11148J\"></sup>forever. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11148K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11148K\"></sup>For he chose Judah as leader, and in the house of Judah my father's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11148L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11148L\"></sup>house, and among my father's sons he took pleasure in me to make me king over all Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11149M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11149M\"></sup>all my sons (for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given me many sons) he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11149N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11149N\"></sup>has chosen Solomon my son to sit on the throne of the kingdom of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> over Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to me, ‘It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11150O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11150O\"></sup>Solomon your son who shall build my house and my courts, for I have chosen him to be my son, and I will be his father.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will establish his kingdom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11151P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11151P\"></sup>forever <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11151Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11151Q\"></sup>if he continues strong in keeping my commandments and my rules, as he is today.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now therefore in the sight of all Israel, the assembly of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and in the hearing of our God, observe and seek out all the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, that you may possess this good land and leave it for an inheritance to your children after you forever.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“And you, Solomon my son, know the God of your father and serve him with a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11153R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11153R\"></sup>whole heart and with a willing mind, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11153S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11153S\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> searches all hearts and understands every plan and thought. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11153T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11153T\"></sup>If you seek him, he will be found by you, but if you forsake him, he will cast you off forever.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Be careful now, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to build a house for the sanctuary; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11154U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11154U\"></sup>be strong and do it.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David gave Solomon his son the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11155V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11155V\"></sup>plan of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11155W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11155W\"></sup>vestibule of the temple, and of its houses, its treasuries, its upper rooms, and its inner chambers, and of the room for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11155X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11155X\"></sup>mercy seat;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and the plan of all that he had in mind for the courts of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, all the surrounding chambers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11156Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11156Y\"></sup>the treasuries of the house of God, and the treasuries for dedicated gifts;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11157Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11157Z\"></sup>divisions of the priests and of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11157AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11157AA\"></sup>Levites, and all the work of the service in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; for all the vessels for the service in the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the weight of gold for all golden vessels for each service, the weight of silver vessels for each service,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the weight of the golden <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11159AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11159AB\"></sup>lampstands and their lamps, the weight of gold for each lampstand and its lamps, the weight of silver for a lampstand and its lamps, according to the use of each lampstand in the service,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the weight of gold for each table for the showbread, the silver for the silver tables,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and pure gold for the forks, the basins and the cups; for the golden bowls and the weight of each; for the silver bowls and the weight of each;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11162AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11162AC\"></sup>altar of incense made of refined gold, and its weight; also his plan for the golden chariot of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11162AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11162AD\"></sup>cherubim that spread their wings and covered the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“All this he made clear to me in writing from the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11163AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11163AE\"></sup>all the work to be done according to the plan.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then David said to Solomon his son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11164AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11164AF\"></sup>“Be strong and courageous and do it. Do not be afraid and do not be dismayed, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, even my God, is with you. He will not leave you or forsake you, until all the work for the service of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is finished.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And behold the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11165AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11165AG\"></sup>divisions of the priests and the Levites for all the service of the house of God; and with you in all the work will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11165AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11165AH\"></sup>every willing man who has skill for any kind of service; also the officers and all the people will be wholly at your command.”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>And David the king said to all the assembly, “Solomon my son, whom alone God has chosen, is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11166A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11166A\"></sup>young and inexperienced, and the work is great, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11166B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11166B\"></sup>the palace will not be for man but for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So I have provided for the house of my God, so far as I was able, the gold for the things of gold, the silver for the things of silver, and the bronze for the things of bronze, the iron for the things of iron, and wood for the things of wood, besides great quantities of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11167C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11167C\"></sup>onyx and stones for setting, antimony, colored stones, all sorts of precious stones and marble.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moreover, in addition to all that I have provided for the holy house, I have a treasure of my own of gold and silver, and because of my devotion to the house of my God I give it to the house of my God:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11169D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11169D\"></sup>3,000 talents of gold, of the gold of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11169E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11169E\"></sup>Ophir, and 7,000 talents of refined silver, for overlaying the walls of the house,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and for all the work to be done by craftsmen, gold for the things of gold and silver for the things of silver. Who then will offer willingly, consecrating himself today to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11171F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11171F\"></sup>the leaders of fathers' houses made their freewill offerings, as did also the leaders of the tribes, the commanders of thousands and of hundreds, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11171G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11171G\"></sup>the officers over the king's work.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They gave for the service of the house of God 5,000 talents and 10,000 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11172H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11172H\"></sup>darics of gold, 10,000 talents of silver, 18,000 talents of bronze and 100,000 talents of iron.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And whoever had precious stones gave them to the treasury of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in the care of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11173I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11173I\"></sup>Jehiel the Gershonite.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the people rejoiced because they had given willingly, for with a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11174J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11174J\"></sup>whole heart they had offered freely to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. David the king also rejoiced greatly.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Therefore David blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the presence of all the assembly. And David said: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11175K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11175K\"></sup>“Blessed are you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel our father, forever and ever.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11176L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11176L\"></sup>Yours, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is the greatness and the power and the glory and the victory and the majesty, for all that is in the heavens and in the earth is yours. Yours is the kingdom, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and you are exalted as head above all.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11177M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11177M\"></sup>Both riches and honor come from you, and you rule over all. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11177N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11177N\"></sup>In your hand are power and might, and in your hand it is to make great and to give strength to all.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And now we thank you, our God, and praise your glorious name.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“But who am I, and what is my people, that we should be able thus to offer willingly? For all things come from you, and of your own have we given you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11180O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11180O\"></sup>For we are strangers before you and sojourners, as all our fathers were. Our days on the earth are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11180P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11180P\"></sup>like a shadow, and there is no abiding.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, all this abundance that we have provided for building you a house for your holy name comes from your hand and is all your own.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I know, my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11182Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11182Q\"></sup>that you test the heart and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11182R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11182R\"></sup>have pleasure in uprightness. In the uprightness of my heart I have freely offered all these things, and now I have seen your people, who are present here, offering freely and joyously to you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, our fathers, keep forever such purposes and thoughts in the hearts of your people, and direct their hearts toward you.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11184S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11184S\"></sup>Grant to Solomon my son a whole heart that he may keep your commandments, your testimonies, and your statutes, performing all, and that he may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11184T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11184T\"></sup>build the palace <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11184U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11184U\"></sup>for which I have made provision.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then David said to all the assembly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11185V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11185V\"></sup>“Bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.” And all the assembly blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11185W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11185W\"></sup>and bowed their heads and paid homage to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to the king.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And they offered sacrifices to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and on the next day offered burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, 1,000 bulls, 1,000 rams, and 1,000 lambs, with their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11186X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11186X\"></sup>drink offerings, and sacrifices in abundance for all Israel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And they ate and drank before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on that day with great gladness.And they made Solomon the son of David king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11187Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11187Y\"></sup>the second time, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11187Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11187Z\"></sup>anointed him as prince for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11187AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11187AA\"></sup>Zadok as priest.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11188AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11188AB\"></sup>Then Solomon sat on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11188AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11188AC\"></sup>throne of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as king in place of David his father. And he prospered, and all Israel obeyed him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the leaders and the mighty men, and also all the sons of King David, pledged their allegiance to King Solomon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made Solomon very <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11190AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11190AD\"></sup>great in the sight of all Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11190AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11190AE\"></sup>bestowed on him such royal majesty as had not been on any king before him in Israel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Thus David the son of Jesse reigned over all Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11192AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11192AF\"></sup>time that he reigned over Israel was forty years. He reigned seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he died <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11193AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11193AG\"></sup>at a good age, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11193AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11193AH\"></sup>full of days, riches, and honor. And Solomon his son reigned in his place.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now the acts of King David, from first to last, are written in the Chronicles <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11194AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11194AI\"></sup>of Samuel the seer, and in the Chronicles of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11194AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11194AJ\"></sup>Nathan the prophet, and in the Chronicles of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11194AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11194AK\"></sup>Gad the seer,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>with accounts of all his rule and his might and of the circumstances <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11195AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11195AL\"></sup>that came upon him and upon Israel and upon all the kingdoms of the countries."
		}
	}
};
